Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.39,0:01:02.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,-大家好  -你好各位\N{\fs90}- Hello. - Hello, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.19,0:01:03.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,各位好 你好\N{\fs90}Greetings. Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.96,0:01:05.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,你好\N{\fs90}Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.06,0:01:09.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,十分感谢\N{\fs90}Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.87,0:01:15.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢 谢谢你们\N{\fs90}Thank you. Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.14,0:01:16.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢\N{\fs90}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.34,0:01:17.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,十分感谢\N{\fs90}Thank you so much,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.54,0:01:19.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,欢迎来到TheGrandTour\N{\fs90}and welcome to The Grand Tour,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.61,0:01:21.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,这周我们来到了\N{\fs90}which this week comes to you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.21,0:01:23.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,阿拉伯联合酋长国\N{\fs90}from the United Arab Emirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.45,0:01:29.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,准确说\N{\fs90}Specifically...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.62,0:01:35.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,准确的说 我们在迪拜\N{\fs90}Specifically, we are in Dubai,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.42,0:01:37.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,这也就意味着 有史以来第一次\N{\fs90}which means, for the first time ever,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.59,0:01:39.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们是帐篷里最穷的三个人\N{\fs90}we are the three poorest people in the tent.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.96,0:01:41.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,-对 对 对\N{\fs90}- Yeah. Yeah, yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.63,0:01:42.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,我是说 看呐\N{\fs90}I mean, look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.80,0:01:44.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,你会想 "他们是怎么把喷泉\N{\fs90}You think, "How do they do that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.20,0:01:45.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,做成那样的"\N{\fs90}with all those fountains?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.50,0:01:47.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要告诉你们一个小秘密\N{\fs90}Well, I'll let you into a little secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.64,0:01:49.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是巴黎水\N{\fs90}It's Perrier water.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.17,0:01:52.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,直喷云霄\N{\fs90}Flinging it up into the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.74,0:01:54.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,前几天我还听到一个段子\N{\fs90}I heard another one the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.41,0:01:55.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,一个出租车司机在一天的繁忙过后\N{\fs90}A taxi driver clearing out his cab
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.04,0:01:57.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,收拾他的车\N{\fs90}after a hard day at work--
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.75,0:02:00.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,雨伞 手机 平常的东西\N{\fs90}umbrella, mobile phone, usual stuff--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.25,0:02:03.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,一根八十万英镑的金条\N{\fs90}£800,000 gold bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.28,0:02:04.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,有人落在那里了\N{\fs90}Someone had left it in there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.65,0:02:08.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,-甚至都没有注意到 -你会的\N{\fs90}- and not even noticed. - You would.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.22,0:02:09.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,注意 据说在这里\N{\fs90}Mind you, that said, here,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.82,0:02:12.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,你可以直接去ATM机拿金条出来\N{\fs90}you can just go to an ATM and get gold out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.59,0:02:14.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,看这个 这可是台ATM机\N{\fs90}Look at this! That's an actual ATM.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.03,0:02:16.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,你设想一下 在凌晨两点\N{\fs90}You know, at two o'clock in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.73,0:02:18.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,"我一个子都没有带"\N{\fs90}"I haven't got an ingot with me."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.70,0:02:20.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是这里就没事了\N{\fs90}But here you're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.54,0:02:23.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,你甚至还可以在这里买轮胎\N{\fs90}You can even buy tyres here, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.07,0:02:26.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,镶满金子和钻石的那种\N{\fs90}Which are studded with gold and diamonds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.14,0:02:29.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,看这个 六十万英镑一套\N{\fs90}Look at this. £600,000 a set.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.91,0:02:32.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,甚至连当局都很阔绰\N{\fs90}Even the authorities are loaded.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.11,0:02:34.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们选了一些当地警车的图片\N{\fs90}We have here a selection of pictures of local police cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.05,0:02:36.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们有大牛\N{\fs90}They have an Aventador.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.78,0:02:39.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们还有SLS\N{\fs90}- They also have an SLS.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.42,0:02:42.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 等着瞧 他们还有一辆布加迪威龙警车\N{\fs90}Yeah. Wait for it. They even have a Veyron police car.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.42,0:02:44.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 显然\N{\fs90}Oh, yeah. Obviously,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.66,0:02:46.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,-因为很有必要 -真的\N{\fs90}- because you need that. - You actually do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.16,0:02:48.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,你需要那些 这很重要\N{\fs90}You need that. It's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.20,0:02:50.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,我还有一张当地救护车的照片\N{\fs90}I've even got a photograph of a local ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.43,0:02:53.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,看这里 一辆莲花\N{\fs90}- Look, here it is. It's a Lotus!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.44,0:02:55.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,不懂这个是怎么投入使用的\N{\fs90}Not quite sure how that works.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.07,0:02:57.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,大概你得打断患者的另外一条腿\N{\fs90}Presumably you have to break the patient's other leg
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.64,0:03:00.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,才能把他放进去\N{\fs90}to actually get him in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.14,0:03:01.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的 -接着是这里的公共交通\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - Then there's public transport.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.88,0:03:05.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,在英国 这是一辆公交车 没错吧\N{\fs90}Now, OK, in the UK, this is a bus, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.45,0:03:06.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的 -让我给你看看\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - Let me show you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.65,0:03:08.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,当地公车的一张照片\N{\fs90}a photograph of a local bus here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.45,0:03:09.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,-瞧 -哇\N{\fs90}- There you go. - Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.29,0:03:13.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,最高时速:250kph\N{\fs90}Top speed: 155mph.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.72,0:03:16.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,值七百万英镑 可载23人\N{\fs90}Costs £7 million. Seats 23 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.69,0:03:18.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,你致电给车主 他会过来接你\N{\fs90}You telephone the owner. He comes and picks you up
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.99,0:03:21.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,把你带到你要去的地方\N{\fs90}and takes you to where you want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.30,0:03:22.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是辆出租车\N{\fs90}Well, that's a taxi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.80,0:03:24.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不 詹姆斯 不是的 -不是吗\N{\fs90}- No, James. No, no, no. - Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.97,0:03:27.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,在迪拜的出租车长这样\N{\fs90}A taxi in Dubai looks like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.87,0:03:29.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦好吧 我就知道\N{\fs90}Oh, right. Yeah, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.74,0:03:32.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,你觉得我在开玩笑吗  看"Uber"\N{\fs90}You think I'm joking? Look, "Uber".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.47,0:03:34.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的 你在这里叫Uber\N{\fs90}Seriously, you call Uber up here,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.64,0:03:37.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们会给你挑 普锐斯还是直升机\N{\fs90}and you're given a choice-- Prius or helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.51,0:03:39.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,哇 你要给司机评级吗\N{\fs90}Wow! Do you get to rate the driver?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.01,0:03:41.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,你觉得他会把手机粘在挡风玻璃上吗\N{\fs90}Do you think he sticks his telephone on the screen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.85,0:03:43.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,就像英国的那些普锐斯一样\N{\fs90}like in Britain in the Prius?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.75,0:03:45.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,"我并不算是一个飞行员\N{\fs90}"I'm not really a pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.25,0:03:47.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,我只是在受训当水管工时顺带做这个"\N{\fs90}I'm doing this while training to be a plumber."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.49,0:03:49.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,"放我出去" 赶紧走\N{\fs90}"I want to get out!" Just get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.12,0:03:51.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们可以开始节目了吗 -好主意\N{\fs90}- Shall we get on with the show? - Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.33,0:03:53.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为在这周的节目里\N{\fs90}Because in our car show this week...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.50,0:03:57.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长摔倒了\N{\fs90}James falls over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.63,0:04:02.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长又摔倒了\N{\fs90}James fall over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.34,0:04:05.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有船长摔倒了\N{\fs90}And James falls over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.71,0:04:11.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,但首先 这里有一点争议\N{\fs90}But first, there's been a bit of an argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.78,0:04:14.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,你看 船长和我最近都刚买了\N{\fs90}You see, James and I both recently bought
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.52,0:04:16.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,五门的德国掀背车\N{\fs90}five-door German hatchbacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.78,0:04:20.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,他的是一辆宝马i3 由电力驱动\N{\fs90}His is a BMW i3, which is powered by electricity,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.96,0:04:25.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我的则是传统的大众高尔夫GTI\N{\fs90}and mine is a conventional Volkswagen Golf GTI.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.23,0:04:27.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 也就是说我的车来自未来\N{\fs90}Yes, meaning my car is from the future
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.93,0:04:29.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,而他的象征过去\N{\fs90}and his is from the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.83,0:04:33.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我显得像开化过的 而他就是一恐龙\N{\fs90}making me enlightened and him a dinosaur.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.17,0:04:36.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们就像这样吵了很久了\N{\fs90}They have been arguing like this for a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.80,0:04:38.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,重要的是 我不怀疑\N{\fs90}The thing is, I don't doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.61,0:04:41.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,在未来电动车会很有用\N{\fs90}that in the future electric cars will work,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.11,0:04:42.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,但现在不行\N{\fs90}but they don't work now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.68,0:04:44.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,-它们可以的 -它们不行 船长\N{\fs90}- Well, they do. - They don't, James!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.41,0:04:45.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,那为什么你要在你的车里\N{\fs90}Well, why did you fit yours
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.91,0:04:48.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,装一个汽油增程发动机\N{\fs90}with a petrol-powered range extender?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.15,0:04:49.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,那只是一个小发电机\N{\fs90}Well, that's just a little generator
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.98,0:04:52.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我需要的时候把电池充满\N{\fs90}that keeps the battery topped up if I need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.92,0:04:55.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,你是说你不能完全依靠新技术\N{\fs90}What you're saying is you can't rely on new technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.39,0:04:56.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有你的座椅\N{\fs90}And your seats, they're made
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.96,0:04:58.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,是用胡佛袋里的东西做的\N{\fs90}from the contents of a Hoover bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.63,0:05:00.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,-嗬 这话\N{\fs90}- Oh, says the man...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.63,0:05:02.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,这话是一个座椅是\N{\fs90}Says the man whose seats are made
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.70,0:05:04.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,用杰基·斯图尔特的破牛仔裤做的人说的\N{\fs90}from Jackie Stewart's old trousers,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.63,0:05:05.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,这又怎样\N{\fs90}which they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.77,0:05:07.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,-那可是... -少废话\N{\fs90}- It's... - Whatever!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.77,0:05:09.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,事实是 在办公室里\N{\fs90}The fact is, in the office,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.10,0:05:10.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们受够了他们的斗嘴\N{\fs90}we decided we'd had enough of them bickering
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.94,0:05:13.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,决定让他们出去进行一场路测\N{\fs90}and told them to go out and do a proper road test.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.61,0:05:16.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们这么做了\N{\fs90}So we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.44,0:05:18.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们从伦敦开始\N{\fs90}We began in London
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.18,0:05:19.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,进行一场大猩猩想要的\N{\fs90}with a real-world test
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.58,0:05:21.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,道路测试\N{\fs90}that Clarkson had thought of.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.48,0:05:22.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,听着船长 我们现在必须看看\N{\fs90}Right, James, we must now see
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.02,0:05:25.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,谁能在最短的时间里打开车后门\N{\fs90}who can open their back door in the shortest time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.59,0:05:27.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,-为啥 -可能会有紧急情况\N{\fs90}- Why? - There could be an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.35,0:05:28.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,人们会想知道的\N{\fs90}People will want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.92,0:05:30.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,各就各位 预备开始 我的开了\N{\fs90}Ready, steady, go! Oh, mine's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.89,0:05:32.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦天呐\N{\fs90}Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.46,0:05:33.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,你不会是要先开了前门\N{\fs90}Have you got to open your front door
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.03,0:05:36.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,才可以打开 老实说 小翻门\N{\fs90}before you open that-- let's be honest-- a flap?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.90,0:05:38.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这才不是翻门  -这就是翻门\N{\fs90}- It's not a flap. - It is a flap.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.80,0:05:40.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,宝马这是在说 在未来\N{\fs90}Are BMW saying that, in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.74,0:05:42.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,孩子们只有三寸宽吗\N{\fs90}children will only be three inches wide?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.80,0:05:44.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,你都在说些啥玩意儿\N{\fs90}What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.07,0:05:45.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,首先 这根本就不是个问题\N{\fs90}For a start, it's hardly a hardship,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.61,0:05:47.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且这可是很大的空间\N{\fs90}and that's an enormous space.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.07,0:05:48.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,你想做这个测试\N{\fs90}You only wanted to do that test
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.71,0:05:50.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,只是因为你犯了个错 他犯了个错\N{\fs90}because you made a mistake. He made a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.61,0:05:51.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,我没有 什么错\N{\fs90}I didn't. What mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.95,0:05:53.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,你错了 你本想要一辆三门高尔夫\N{\fs90}You did. You wanted a three-door Golf,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.78,0:05:55.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,但你没填对表\N{\fs90}and you didn't fill the form in properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.25,0:05:57.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我知道的 你都不会打勾勾\N{\fs90}I know that. You can't tick boxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.02,0:05:59.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,五门的更好看\N{\fs90}Five doors are better-looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.39,0:06:00.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 才没有\N{\fs90}No, they're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.76,0:06:02.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有人会想要一辆五门高尔夫GTI\N{\fs90}Nobody ever wanted a five-door Golf GTI.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.62,0:06:04.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这好土 -我们快上路再来谈谈钱\N{\fs90}- It's really naff. - We've got to get on and talk about money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.79,0:06:06.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,他还想要一辆红色的\N{\fs90}He also wanted a red one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.26,0:06:08.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是那个他也没填对\N{\fs90}He didn't fill that bit in properly, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.10,0:06:20.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车 加上很多很多的配件\N{\fs90}This car, with many, many optional extras,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.27,0:06:22.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,才三万六千英镑\N{\fs90}was £36,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.84,0:06:25.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是船长的宝马i3\N{\fs90}Whereas James May's BMW i3 was...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.98,0:06:28.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 不如让我们来一探究竟\N{\fs90}Well... let's find out, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.02,0:06:31.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,你的i3多少钱\N{\fs90}How much was your i3?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.49,0:06:33.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,它四万磅\N{\fs90}Well, it was £40,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.45,0:06:35.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是我从政府那里拿了五千英镑补贴\N{\fs90}but I got £5,000 back from the government,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.96,0:06:37.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以实际价格三万五千英镑\N{\fs90}so actually it's £35,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.66,0:06:39.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,比你的低 我想\N{\fs90}which is less than yours, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.29,0:06:41.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,你从政府那里拿了\N{\fs90}You were given, by the government,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.86,0:06:45.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,五千英镑纳税人的钱\N{\fs90}£5,000 of taxpayers' money
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.77,0:06:47.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以你才可以买这车\N{\fs90}so you could buy that car?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.04,0:06:50.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,又不是我定的规则 你又不能不收\N{\fs90}I didn't make the rules. You can't turn it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.67,0:06:52.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,这又不像披头士的官佐勋章\N{\fs90}It's not like the Beatles' OBE.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.41,0:06:53.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,太不要脸了\N{\fs90}That is obscene!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.98,0:06:56.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,我是说 船长是个有钱人\N{\fs90}I mean, James May is a wealthy man,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.08,0:07:00.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是那公交车司机却为他的车付钱\N{\fs90}but that bus driver has bought his car for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.38,0:07:02.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,说好的公平呢\N{\fs90}Where's the justice in that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.39,0:07:07.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,你在为他的车付钱 你知道吗\N{\fs90}You're paying for his car. Do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.32,0:07:08.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,你已经付过了\N{\fs90}You have paid for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.69,0:07:11.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,只是想让你知道 你给他的车付了钱\N{\fs90}Just so you know, you've paid for his car.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.29,0:07:14.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,你帮船长买车 他谢过你了没\N{\fs90}Has James May thanked you for buying his car for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.70,0:07:16.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,杰里米对此有点意见\N{\fs90}Jeremy will have an opinion on this,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.36,0:07:19.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,尽管他买了一个农场 好多年了\N{\fs90}despite having bought a farm on which, for many years,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.77,0:07:23.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,却啥也不种\N{\fs90}he was paid to not grow anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.81,0:07:25.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里的拥堵费\N{\fs90}Congestion charge here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.14,0:07:27.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,开到市中心要11.5英镑\N{\fs90}It's £11.50 to drive into the centre.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.37,0:07:29.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我可不用 -当然不用\N{\fs90}- Not for me, it isn't. -Of course it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.71,0:07:32.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,那个出租车司机 他正在帮你付拥堵费吗\N{\fs90}The taxi driver, is he paying for your congestion charge?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.45,0:07:35.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想所有人都得付一点\N{\fs90}I suppose everybody must pay a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.72,0:07:39.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长 船长 打家劫舍\N{\fs90}* James May, James May Stealing from the rich *
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.29,0:07:42.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长 船长 巧取豪夺\N{\fs90}* James May, James May Stealing from the poor *
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.82,0:07:46.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,他劫富不济贫 劫贫不济富\N{\fs90}* He steals from the rich He steals from the poor *
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.89,0:07:49.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,次次如此 贪得无厌\N{\fs90}* And once more, wants it all *
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.63,0:07:51.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,骇人听闻\N{\fs90}* That's appalling *
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.77,0:07:54.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,差不多就这样\N{\fs90}It nearly works.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.60,0:07:57.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,我已经受够了\N{\fs90}I'd had enough of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.17,0:07:59.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我提出了一个新法子来证明\N{\fs90}so I came up with a new way of trying to prove
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.07,0:08:01.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的车比他的好\N{\fs90}my car was better than his.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.41,0:08:08.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长我能问问你 为什么要把我带到伦敦机场来\N{\fs90}James, can I just ask, why have you brought me to London Airport?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.55,0:08:13.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我要证明我的车比你的快\N{\fs90}Because I want to prove that my car is faster than yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.29,0:08:15.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,这很可笑 因为我刚刚听到你说\N{\fs90}That's funny, because I just heard you say
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.19,0:08:16.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,你的车要比我的快\N{\fs90}that your car's faster than mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.76,0:08:18.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 就是这样\N{\fs90}Yeah. Yeah, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.63,0:08:20.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,-167马力 -嗯哼\N{\fs90}- 167 horsepower. - Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.56,0:08:24.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的有性能套件 所以有227马力\N{\fs90}Mine has the performance pack, so it produces 227.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.87,0:08:25.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,-真的嘛 -是的\N{\fs90}- Does it? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.03,0:08:27.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是官方数据对吧\N{\fs90}That's the official figure, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.43,0:08:28.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fs90}Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.47,0:08:29.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,-来自大众 -是的\N{\fs90}- From VW? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.64,0:08:32.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,-而你竟然相信他们 -是的\N{\fs90}- And you believe them? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.87,0:08:34.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的听着 我知道你的意思\N{\fs90}All right, listen, I know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.88,0:08:37.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,0-150加速赛\N{\fs90}Drag race: 0-150.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.31,0:08:39.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,不要\N{\fs90}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.31,0:08:41.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,在没有达成一致之后\N{\fs90}Having not agreed on that,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.65,0:08:43.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们在终点的设置上\N{\fs90}we then failed to agree
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.08,0:08:45.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,也没有达成一致\N{\fs90}on where the finishing line should be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.59,0:08:48.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长想要一个短距离比赛\N{\fs90}James wanted a short race...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.42,0:08:49.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我不想\N{\fs90}and I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.96,0:08:54.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,-妥了吧  -才没有 太短了\N{\fs90}- Compromise. - It isn't. That's too short.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.33,0:08:56.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,-才不短 这刚好 -就是短了\N{\fs90}- It's not. It's exactly right. - It is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.36,0:08:59.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是最终 我们还是准备出发了\N{\fs90}But eventually, we were ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.27,0:09:05.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在 有件事需要记住 观众们\N{\fs90}Now, the thing to remember, viewers,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.94,0:09:07.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,一台电动机\N{\fs90}is that an electric motor
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.31,0:09:09.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,可以在几乎零转速下\N{\fs90}delivers enormous torque from nothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.94,0:09:11.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,就提供大量的扭矩\N{\fs90}from really low down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.48,0:09:12.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以在短距离里\N{\fs90}So over a short distance,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.81,0:09:14.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,我毫无疑问可以碾压\N{\fs90}I should absolutely cream this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.95,0:09:16.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们开始吧\N{\fs90}Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.48,0:09:18.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,DCC 正常\N{\fs90}DCC-- normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.52,0:09:20.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,转向 正常\N{\fs90}Steering-- normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.82,0:09:23.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,驾驶模式  环保\N{\fs90}Drive-- eco.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.26,0:09:26.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,赢船长没必要毁了我的车\N{\fs90}No point in ruining my own car to win this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.71,0:09:47.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,不用着急\N{\fs90}No need to rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.88,0:09:51.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要赢了 哦耶\N{\fs90}I'm winning. Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.92,0:09:56.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,我还领先着\N{\fs90}I'm still winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.22,0:09:58.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我们超过它 加油啊小高尔夫\N{\fs90}Let's go get him. Come on, Golfy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.59,0:10:00.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 不\N{\fs90}No. No!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.93,0:10:03.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,很轻快 但是\N{\fs90}Quite sprightly, but er...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.87,0:10:06.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,但没我想的那么轻快\N{\fs90}not sprightly enough, methinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.87,0:10:08.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,再见了船长\N{\fs90}See you, James.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.11,0:10:18.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,我让未来在电视上看起来\N{\fs90}Bah! I've made the future look rubbish
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.61,0:10:20.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,就像堆垃圾\N{\fs90}on the television.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.55,0:10:23.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,接着 为了让它看上去更糟\N{\fs90}And then, to make it look even worse,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.15,0:10:24.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,我告诉这利益窃取者\N{\fs90}I told the benefit scrounger
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.95,0:10:26.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们要启程去德文郡\N{\fs90}that we were setting off for Devon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.99,0:10:30.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么我们要去德文郡\N{\fs90}Erm... Why are we going to Devon?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.86,0:10:32.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我这里有今晚的两张票\N{\fs90}Because we have two tickets tonight
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.99,0:10:35.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,去看罗杰·达尔特雷在从Who单飞之后\N{\fs90}to see Roger Daltrey out of the Who
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.90,0:10:39.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,在达特缪尔的酒吧里表演\N{\fs90}perform at a pub on Dartmoor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.37,0:10:40.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们难道就不能等到\N{\fs90}Couldn't we just wait for him
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.87,0:10:42.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,他来伦敦表演的时候吗\N{\fs90}to come and maybe perform in London?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.57,0:10:44.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,-因为我确信他会来 -才不要\N{\fs90}- Because I'm sure he will. - Well, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.94,0:10:47.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为这差不多要开三百二十公里\N{\fs90}Because it's a 200-mile drive, or thereabouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.14,0:10:48.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,这给了我们一个机会\N{\fs90}it'll give us an opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.88,0:10:51.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看我们的车在现实世界里表现如何\N{\fs90}to see how our cars work in the real world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.38,0:10:53.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,他的意思是这是个机会来让他宣称\N{\fs90}What he means is it's an opportunity for him to claim
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.95,0:10:58.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,过去的车是多么出众\N{\fs90}that the car of the past is superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.22,0:11:00.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了证明不是这样 我需要充满\N{\fs90}To prove it wasn't, I needed to top up
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.35,0:11:03.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,在加速赛中损耗的电力\N{\fs90}the charge I'd lost by doing the drag race.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.99,0:11:06.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,好 如果我查卫星导航\N{\fs90}Right, if I look at settings on my satnav,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.96,0:11:10.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,就可以看到充电和加油站在哪里\N{\fs90}I can look at where all the charging and petrol stations are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.50,0:11:13.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,我甚至还能知道我将在\N{\fs90}I can even tell what sort of charging point
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.13,0:11:15.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,哪个充电桩上充电\N{\fs90}I am being offered,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.07,0:11:19.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管我有没有对的卡\N{\fs90}whether or not I have the right card for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.31,0:11:22.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,很快 我就找到了我正寻找的东西\N{\fs90}And soon, we found exactly what I was looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.32,0:11:36.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这就是未来 -换一个\N{\fs90}- It's the future. - Another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.36,0:11:39.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,-太丢脸了 -闭嘴\N{\fs90}- Oh, that's such a shame. - Oh, shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.29,0:11:41.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我的电池电力不够我\N{\fs90}Because I didn't have enough juice in the batteries
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.70,0:11:43.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,开到下一个充电点\N{\fs90}to make the next charge point,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.60,0:11:46.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,我打开了我的汽油发电机\N{\fs90}I had to turn on my petrol generator,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.53,0:11:48.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,以免电量更少了\N{\fs90}which stopped them going even flatter,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.20,0:11:52.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且使用了专业环保驾驶模式\N{\fs90}and engaged ECO PRO+ driving mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.61,0:11:55.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,这意味着我只能开90kph\N{\fs90}It does mean I have to do 56mph.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.98,0:12:00.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是专业环保模式的最高时速\N{\fs90}That's where ECO PRO+ sets the maximum speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.28,0:12:02.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为这样你能得到最大的续航里程\N{\fs90}because that way you get the maximum range.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.28,0:12:04.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这也意味着我实际上是个货车司机\N{\fs90}But it means I'm effectively a lorry driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.82,0:12:07.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我在专业生态模式 我不能开空调\N{\fs90}Because I'm in ECO PRO, I don't get any air-conditioning
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.75,0:12:09.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者任何温控\N{\fs90}or climate control at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.32,0:12:11.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为那费电\N{\fs90}because that wastes electricity,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.43,0:12:14.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以这车在缓慢行驶\N{\fs90}so the car is slowly steaming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.70,0:12:16.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,它现在在警告我 它说\N{\fs90}It's now warning me. It says,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.06,0:12:18.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,"找个充电站 你个白痴"\N{\fs90}"Find a charge station, you idiot!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.47,0:12:22.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,你到底得缺多少根筋 才会说\N{\fs90}How many screws do you have to have loose before you say
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.27,0:12:24.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,"是的 我要买一辆车\N{\fs90}"Yes, I'm gonna buy a car,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.54,0:12:27.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,在电量低的时候\N{\fs90}which, when it's running low on power,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.07,0:12:29.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,只能开到12kph\N{\fs90}has to be driven at 8mph,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.54,0:12:32.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,空调和灯都关着\N{\fs90}with the air conditioning off, and the lights off,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.11,0:12:34.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,暖气也关了 收音机也关了"\N{\fs90}and the heater off, and the radio off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.65,0:12:38.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,你何必要这样\N{\fs90}Why would you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.15,0:12:40.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,在护送船长\N{\fs90}After several lifetimes
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.12,0:12:42.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,开了几个世纪之后\N{\fs90}of driving in convoy with James,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.19,0:12:43.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们终于找到\N{\fs90}we finally found
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.36,0:12:45.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,一个能用的充电点\N{\fs90}a charge point that worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.93,0:12:49.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是这样\N{\fs90}That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.33,0:12:50.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这就好了 -是的\N{\fs90}- It's done? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.56,0:12:52.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,你不用站着盯着它\N{\fs90}You don't have to stand and watch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.07,0:12:53.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不像汽油 我们可以走开\N{\fs90}It's not like petrol. We can go off
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.60,0:12:56.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,喝杯咖啡 吃点面包\N{\fs90}and have a cup of coffee, a sticky bun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.34,0:12:58.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这要花多久 -一个多小时吧\N{\fs90}- How long is it gonna take? - An hour or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.74,0:13:00.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,-一个小时 -是的\N{\fs90}- An hour? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.31,0:13:03.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,给它充满 要花多少钱\N{\fs90}How much does it cost... to fill it up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.58,0:13:04.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,一分都不用\N{\fs90}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.31,0:13:08.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,-什么  -这是免费的\N{\fs90}- What? - It's free.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.08,0:13:10.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这怎么可能是免费的 -就是免费的\N{\fs90}- How could it be free? - It's free.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.25,0:13:12.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,你必须得有卡 但是这不花钱\N{\fs90}You have to get the card, but it doesn't cost...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.15,0:13:14.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,-办那卡要多少钱  -一分都不用\N{\fs90}- How much does the card cost? - Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.52,0:13:16.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,你只要在网上填张表\N{\fs90}You fill a form in on the Internet,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.12,0:13:17.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,它就会邮寄过来\N{\fs90}and it comes in the post.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.49,0:13:19.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我还在为你付\N{\fs90}So I'm paying for your fuel--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.06,0:13:20.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,油钱...不对电钱？\N{\fs90}well, your electricity-- as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.86,0:13:22.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,可能吧\N{\fs90}Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.20,0:13:23.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,我真是震惊了\N{\fs90}I'm just staggered by this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.63,0:13:24.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,这太不公正了\N{\fs90}This is iniquitous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.07,0:13:27.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,在虚度了一会光阴之后\N{\fs90}After killing time for a few minutes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.77,0:13:29.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要试着去赚些钱\N{\fs90}I'm just gonna try and win some money
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.50,0:13:32.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,来付船长这些年的暖气费\N{\fs90}to pay for James May's heating bill this year,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.27,0:13:35.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,这无疑让我很不爽\N{\fs90}which... will undoubtedly be down to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.84,0:13:38.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我决定我再也不想等了\N{\fs90}...I decided I couldn't be bothered to wait any more,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.65,0:13:41.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我要用老方法加了油\N{\fs90}so I recharged the old-fashioned way
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.65,0:13:44.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,片刻之后 再次上路\N{\fs90}and, in moments, was back on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.19,0:13:49.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,英国电网只供\N{\fs90}Britain only produces
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.09,0:13:53.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,实际用电需求105%的电\N{\fs90}5% more power than it actually consumes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.09,0:13:57.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,现状正是如此 所以如果每个人都买电动车\N{\fs90}That's now. So if everybody starts buying electric cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.33,0:13:59.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,发电站会应付不过来\N{\fs90}the power stations won't be able to cope.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.40,0:14:00.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,电力就会中断\N{\fs90}There'll be power cuts,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.80,0:14:03.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,接着就是抢劫和骚乱\N{\fs90}and then there will be looting and anarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.27,0:14:05.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,都是船长干的好事\N{\fs90}That's what James is doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.11,0:14:08.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,他让英国跪了\N{\fs90}He is bringing Britain to its knees.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.15,0:14:18.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,好啊\N{\fs90}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.49,0:14:20.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里有些给杰里米的东西\N{\fs90}Here's something for Jeremy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.99,0:14:22.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,希望他有个CD播放器\N{\fs90}Assuming he's got a CD player.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.52,0:14:24.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,他的高尔夫GTI里\N{\fs90}He's probably got a cassette player
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.56,0:14:25.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,可能还有卡带机\N{\fs90}in his Golf GTI.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.03,0:14:27.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,事实上\N{\fs90}Actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.33,0:14:30.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长大错特错\N{\fs90}May couldn't have been more wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.50,0:14:33.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车可能来自过去 但是瞧瞧这个\N{\fs90}This car may be from the past, but check this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.60,0:14:35.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,它正在加速 你可能听到了\N{\fs90}It's accelerating now, you can probably hear that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.84,0:14:37.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是我可并没有干这个\N{\fs90}but I'm not doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.14,0:14:38.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的前视雷达\N{\fs90}The radar in front of me
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.87,0:14:40.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,正在帮我与前车\N{\fs90}is maintaining a safe distance
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.87,0:14:43.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,保持一个安全距离\N{\fs90}behind the car in front.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.51,0:14:45.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,他快我就快\N{\fs90}He goes faster, I go faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.45,0:14:46.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,他慢我也慢\N{\fs90}He slows down, I slow down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.75,0:14:48.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,有车现在变到中间车道\N{\fs90}Car pulling out now into the middle lane.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.15,0:14:49.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车能检测到\N{\fs90}The car will sense that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.52,0:14:51.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 它现在正让我退到\N{\fs90}Yeah. It's now dropping me
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.29,0:14:52.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,那辆车的后面\N{\fs90}back from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.55,0:14:54.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,我甚至都不用转向\N{\fs90}I don't even have to steer,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.59,0:14:56.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为它会自己保持在白线内\N{\fs90}because it'll keep itself between the white lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.02,0:14:58.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,看\N{\fs90}Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.16,0:14:59.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,谷歌一直在大惊小怪\N{\fs90}Google is making a big fuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.93,0:15:01.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,"看我们有多聪明\N{\fs90}"Ooh, aren't we clever?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.30,0:15:02.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们在造能自动行驶的车"\N{\fs90}We're making a self-driving car."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.90,0:15:05.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,已经有了 我开的就是\N{\fs90}It's already here! I'm driving it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.37,0:15:07.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,它来自1978年\N{\fs90}And it's from 1978.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.67,0:15:12.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,在充了一个小时之后\N{\fs90}After an hour's charging,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.37,0:15:15.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,我又继续上路\N{\fs90}I was back on the move.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.18,0:15:17.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,我倒是觉得在高速公路上的服务站\N{\fs90}I actually think the service station on the motorway
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.51,0:15:19.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,应该为电动车车主专设一区\N{\fs90}should have an electric-car driver section,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.98,0:15:21.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,在那里 你懂得\N{\fs90}where there are, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.55,0:15:23.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,得有十分复杂的拼图游戏和大富翁\N{\fs90}very complicated jigsaw puzzles and a Monopoly set,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.85,0:15:26.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者一些填色图画\N{\fs90}or maybe some painting-by-numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.32,0:15:31.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有270公里\N{\fs90}It is 170 miles to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.26,0:15:34.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,天哪看看 一直要开到那里\N{\fs90}God, look at it. It's all the way down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.56,0:15:36.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,在很前方\N{\fs90}Many miles ahead,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.20,0:15:37.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,我正忙着开启\N{\fs90}I was busy firing up
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.70,0:15:41.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,GTI的苹果CarPlay系统\N{\fs90}the GTI's Apple CarPlay system.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.10,0:15:44.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,我现在正打算给船长发个信息\N{\fs90}Right, I'm gonna send James May a text message now,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.37,0:15:46.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,在很多车里这都是违法的\N{\fs90}which would be illegal in most cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.37,0:15:47.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,但在这车里可不是\N{\fs90}but not in this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.04,0:15:50.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,请问你想给谁发送消息\N{\fs90}To whom should I send your message?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.78,0:15:52.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,梅\N{\fs90}May.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.45,0:15:55.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,您在说什么 啊哦 出了些问题\N{\fs90}What was that again? Uh-oh, something's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.22,0:15:56.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,请您再试一次\N{\fs90}Can you try again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.02,0:15:58.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,把这段切了\N{\fs90}Edit that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.08,0:15:59.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,我应该发送给谁\N{\fs90}To whom shall I send it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.92,0:16:01.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,梅\N{\fs90}May.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.66,0:16:05.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不知道你说"巴里"的意思\N{\fs90}I don't know what you mean by "Barry".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.66,0:16:08.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我应该发送给谁 -我没说"巴里"\N{\fs90}- To whom shall I send it? - I didn't say "Barry".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.26,0:16:10.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,梅\N{\fs90}May.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.30,0:16:13.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,这可不行啊 大众 得了吧\N{\fs90}This is not doing well, Volkswagen. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.80,0:16:17.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 您想对梅说什么\N{\fs90}OK. What do you want to say to May?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.14,0:16:18.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,"梅 你这个十足的白痴"\N{\fs90}"May, you're a blithering idiot,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.97,0:16:22.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,你那蠢车毁了我的一天\N{\fs90}and your stupid car is ruining my day."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.68,0:16:25.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,您发送给梅的消息如下\N{\fs90}Your message to May says,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.35,0:16:28.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,"你的兄弟是白痴 还有你那蠢车已经准备好了"\N{\fs90}"Your brother is idiot and your stupid car is ready."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.58,0:16:29.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,准备好发送了吗\N{\fs90}Ready to send it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.42,0:16:35.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,"你的兄弟是白痴"\N{\fs90}"Your brother is idiot"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.72,0:16:38.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,啥 他从来我见过我兄弟\N{\fs90}What? He's never met my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.12,0:16:40.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,他怎么知道他是白痴\N{\fs90}How does he know he's an idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.89,0:16:42.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我下了高速\N{\fs90}Because I'd turned off the motorway
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.90,0:16:45.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,选了更能直达达特穆尔的路线\N{\fs90}to take the more direct route to Dartmoor,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.17,0:16:48.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得最好通知船长一声\N{\fs90}I thought I'd better let James know that as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.90,0:16:55.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,我打算走A34和A303公路\N{\fs90}Erm... I'm going on the A34 and the A303.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.34,0:16:56.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,在那里等你\N{\fs90}I'll see you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.18,0:17:01.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,您给梅的消息写道\N{\fs90}Your message to May says,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.08,0:17:04.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,"我要去三个RC的第一层"\N{\fs90}"I'm going on the first floor of the three RC."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.15,0:17:05.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,准备发送吗\N{\fs90}Ready to send it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.92,0:17:13.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,与此同时 我选了更长的高速公路路线\N{\fs90} I, meanwhile, was using the longer motorway route
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.19,0:17:15.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为这里有更多的充电站\N{\fs90}because there'd be more charging points.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.90,0:17:17.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,于是我踩下了油门\N{\fs90}But I had my foot down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.87,0:17:24.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在 象征未来的电动车\N{\fs90}And now... the electric car of the future
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.31,0:17:28.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,正在超一台保时捷911 Turbo S\N{\fs90}is overtaking a Porsche 911 Turbo S.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.04,0:17:30.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,瞧好了\N{\fs90}There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.94,0:17:34.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,我开着一辆车在高速公路上\N{\fs90}I'm driving along in a car on the motorway
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.05,0:17:37.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,以标准限速\N{\fs90}at motorway speeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.08,0:17:38.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,超过了所有人\N{\fs90}overtaking everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.72,0:17:42.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦不 自从我加满油以后\N{\fs90}Oh, no. Since I filled up,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.56,0:17:46.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,我已经用了八分之一了\N{\fs90}I've used... an eighth of a tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.13,0:17:47.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦不\N{\fs90}Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.73,0:17:53.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,自从我深入德文郡的郊区\N{\fs90}And soon I was deep in the Devon countryside,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.10,0:17:56.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,这优秀的高速巡航利器\N{\fs90}where my excellent motorway cruising machine
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.40,0:17:58.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,变成了一辆真正的GTI\N{\fs90}had become a GTI.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.78,0:18:06.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在我们在运动模式了\N{\fs90}We're in full sport mode now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.72,0:18:13.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,它有个令人惊讶的前差速器\N{\fs90}It's got an astonishing front differential,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.62,0:18:16.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以你可以大力地将车驶入每个弯道\N{\fs90}so you can hurl the car into any corner
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.49,0:18:18.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,以任何你能想到的速度\N{\fs90}at any speed that takes your fancy,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.89,0:18:22.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且知道你可以成功的出弯\N{\fs90}knowing you're gonna come out on the other side OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.07,0:18:26.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,我没开玩笑 在这样的路上\N{\fs90}I'm not kidding. On a road like this
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.77,0:18:29.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,湿叶和泥巴到处都是\N{\fs90}with wet leaves and mud everywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.54,0:18:34.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车可以和任何法拉利一样快\N{\fs90}this car is as fast as any Ferrari.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.24,0:18:35.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,它就是如此\N{\fs90}It just is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.18,0:18:41.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,在接下来的很长一段时间里\N{\fs90}Many hours from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.75,0:18:43.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长会像这样一直念叨着\N{\fs90}James May's going to be coming along here saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.92,0:18:46.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,"我还有13%的电量和2%的油"\N{\fs90}"Right, I've got 13% battery and 2% fuel,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.05,0:18:50.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以如果我油耗百公里17升 可以..."\N{\fs90}so if I do 13.8 miles to the gallon, I should..."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.96,0:18:52.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,明明可以做松油门甩尾\N{\fs90}Who wants to do maths
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.13,0:18:54.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么还要做算数\N{\fs90}when they could do lift-off oversteer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.16,0:19:00.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,在i3 多亏了我娴熟的驾驶技术\N{\fs90}In the i3, thanks to my exuberant driving,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.77,0:19:03.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,我确实得做些算数\N{\fs90}I was indeed having to do some maths.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:06.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,能源管理更新\N{\fs90}Energy management update:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.77,0:19:10.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果我继续这么开\N{\fs90}I have 36 miles of electric power remaining,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.64,0:19:12.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,电力还可以开58公里\N{\fs90}if I'm driving like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.51,0:19:15.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有55公里的汽油剩余\N{\fs90}and 34 miles of petrol range left.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.95,0:19:17.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我得在这些服务区停车\N{\fs90}So I'm going to stop at these services
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.95,0:19:20.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,再填满那小油箱\N{\fs90}and I'm going to fill up the little fuel tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.53,0:19:26.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,9英镑 这实在是\N{\fs90}Nine quid. That is absolutely...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.46,0:19:27.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,其实我加多了\N{\fs90}I've overfilled it, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.57,0:19:33.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你开一辆GTI\N{\fs90}If you drive a GTI,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.33,0:19:36.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,你会更快地到你想去的地方\N{\fs90}you're going to get to where you're going more quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.84,0:19:39.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就意味着你会见到更多的人\N{\fs90}which means you're going to meet more people,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.64,0:19:43.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,有更多的阅历 学到更多的东西\N{\fs90}have more experiences, learn more stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.28,0:19:45.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,速度让你聪明\N{\fs90}Speed makes you cleverer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.85,0:19:53.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,同理 如果你开一辆宝马i3\N{\fs90}Whereas, if you drive a BMW i3,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.02,0:19:55.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,你去哪里都得迟\N{\fs90}you're gonna get everywhere late.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.56,0:19:57.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,你会错过很多事\N{\fs90}You're gonna miss out on things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.59,0:20:02.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,你会错过戏剧 文化 诗歌\N{\fs90}You'll miss out on theatre, culture, poetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.26,0:20:03.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有爱\N{\fs90}Love.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.90,0:20:06.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,你会徒有人类空荡的躯壳\N{\fs90}You'll be a hollowed-out husk of a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.94,0:20:12.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,"连接你的车辆并确认"\N{\fs90}"Connect your vehicle and validate."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.11,0:20:18.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,"确认"是什么意思 我已经确认了啊\N{\fs90}What do they mean, "validate"? I've already validated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.85,0:20:22.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,到了 我的探索结束了\N{\fs90}And here we are. My quest is at an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.75,0:20:25.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,在对的时间 万事皆佳\N{\fs90}I'm in good time. All is well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.25,0:20:26.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且我还受到了款待\N{\fs90}And I was in for a treat,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.02,0:20:29.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为和罗杰·达尔特雷同台的是\N{\fs90}because joining Roger Daltrey on stage
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.09,0:20:32.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,传奇的吉他手威尔科·约翰逊\N{\fs90}was legendary guitarist Wilko Johnson.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.79,0:20:34.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,那个传说中的威尔科·约翰逊\N{\fs90}The fabulous Wilko Johnson!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.26,0:20:42.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,"站点正在等待来自车辆的充电请求\N{\fs90}"Station waiting for a charge request from the vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.64,0:20:45.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,初始化 充电中"\N{\fs90}Initialisation. Charging."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.17,0:20:48.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,这没在充电\N{\fs90}It's not charging.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.51,0:20:55.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,*等一下 宝贝*\N{\fs90}* Well, wait a minute, baby *
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.55,0:20:57.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,*你要干什么*\N{\fs90}* Well, whatcha gonna do? *
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.89,0:21:02.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,观众们 我们现在所处的状况是\N{\fs90}OK, viewers, here is where we're at.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.62,0:21:05.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,最后一个充电站不管用\N{\fs90}That last charging station wasn't working.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.93,0:21:08.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,电量还剩下90公里\N{\fs90}We have about 60 miles to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.76,0:21:11.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以答案是\N{\fs90}So the answer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.60,0:21:13.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,环保模式驾驶\N{\fs90}eco driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.07,0:21:15.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,*我漂浮在街道之上*\N{\fs90}* Then I float on Down the street *
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.87,0:21:18.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,*脸上挂着的笑容*\N{\fs90}* Smiling at the faces
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.64,0:21:20.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,*我所见如是*\N{\fs90}* That I meet *
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.95,0:21:27.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不能切换到快速模式\N{\fs90}I'm not switching it into fast mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.71,0:21:29.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,这太浪费了\N{\fs90}It's too wasteful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.85,0:21:34.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,*然后我回到了家*\N{\fs90}* Then I'm going back home *
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.19,0:21:42.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,离酒吧还有29公里\N{\fs90}It is 18 miles to the pub.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.90,0:21:46.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我还剩下26公里的电力\N{\fs90}I have 16 miles of electric left.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.67,0:21:49.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有什么东西可以关掉吗\N{\fs90}Is there anything else I can turn off?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.91,0:21:58.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,最终 经过了很多里程的焦虑之后\N{\fs90}Finally, after much range anxiety...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.44,0:22:00.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,罗杰·达尔特雷 我来了\N{\fs90}Roger Daltrey, here I come!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.75,0:22:01.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我做到了\N{\fs90}...I made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.12,0:22:11.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢你们的到来 晚安\N{\fs90}Thanks for coming, and good night!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.63,0:22:13.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,卧槽\N{\fs90}Oh, cock!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.43,0:22:18.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以等等\N{\fs90}- So... Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.60,0:22:22.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你的车是未来 -是的\N{\fs90}- Your car of the future... - Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.80,0:22:24.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,两个充电站\N{\fs90}Two of the charging points
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.37,0:22:27.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,在你这简单的旅程里 两个坏了\N{\fs90}you went to on that simple journey, two were broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.07,0:22:28.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 这很不寻常 但重点是\N{\fs90}Yes, that is very unusual. But the point is,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.01,0:22:30.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果我可以\N{\fs90}if I'd been allowed to set off
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.01,0:22:33.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,以满电满油的状态开始\N{\fs90}with a full electric charge and a full little fuel tank,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.85,0:22:36.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,我可以到终点 公认地开90kph\N{\fs90}I could have got there-- admittedly a lot at 56mph--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.18,0:22:38.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且我只用停下来一次\N{\fs90}but I would have done it with one stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.32,0:22:40.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,90kph 未来听起来真无趣 船长\N{\fs90}56mph. The future does sound boring, James.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.95,0:22:43.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且你还会错过演出\N{\fs90}And you still would have missed the gig.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.52,0:22:45.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,那片子过时了\N{\fs90}That film is out of date.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.19,0:22:47.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,你再也不会从政府那里拿到五千英镑了\N{\fs90}You don't get £5,000 from the government any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.83,0:22:52.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你只会拿到四千五百英镑 -人们该如何应对啊\N{\fs90}- You only get £4,500. - How will people cope?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.70,0:22:54.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得我们所做的证明了\N{\fs90}I think what we've done there is prove
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.30,0:22:56.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,他的车现在还不值得买\N{\fs90}his car is not really worth buying just yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.77,0:22:59.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,-别争了 就不是 它还没完善 -别又开始了\N{\fs90}- Don't argue. It isn't. It's not quite finished. - Don't start again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.71,0:23:01.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我们继续之前 我还要再说一点\N{\fs90}Before we move on, I want to tell you a little bit more
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.98,0:23:03.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,关于大众的短信系统\N{\fs90}about that Volkswagen system of texting.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.01,0:23:06.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为有天我在车里试着发短信\N{\fs90}Cos I was using that to send a text from my car
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.88,0:23:08.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,给我的小女儿\N{\fs90}the other day to my youngest daughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.85,0:23:11.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在结尾打了四个亲亲 这很正常\N{\fs90}and I put four kisses at the end, which is normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.85,0:23:15.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说"X-X-X-X" 而这是她收到的\N{\fs90}And I said "X-X-X-X", OK? This is what she got.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.76,0:23:17.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦不\N{\fs90}- Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.96,0:23:19.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就尴尬了\N{\fs90}Oh, that is awkward!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.73,0:23:24.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,她回复了什么\N{\fs90}What did she say?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.07,0:23:29.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,- 简直尴尬  - 你试试连着说几个X\N{\fs90}- Oh, that is awkward. - Say it, "X-X-X-X".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.54,0:23:30.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是这个结果\N{\fs90}That's what comes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.70,0:23:32.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,她从自己爹那收到这样的信息\N{\fs90}What sort of face did she pull
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.54,0:23:34.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,是个什么表情\N{\fs90}when she got that from her dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.57,0:23:35.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,想吐\N{\fs90}Vomitous. Vomitous.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.81,0:23:37.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们再没联系过\N{\fs90}We haven't spoken since.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.14,0:23:38.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,卡娅 对不起 是车的问题\N{\fs90}Katya, I'm sorry. It was the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.91,0:23:40.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,-继续节目  -好主意\N{\fs90}- Move on! - Yes, let's move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.91,0:23:45.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,是时候参观一下聊天公司的总部\N{\fs90}It is now time for us to visit the headquarters of Chat & Co,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.22,0:23:48.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然 其总部位于唠嗑街\N{\fs90}who are, of course, based on Conversation Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.03,0:23:59.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,最好的一期 好的 首先\N{\fs90}Best one yet. Anyway, we begin...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.53,0:24:01.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,首先来说说迪拜\N{\fs90}We begin with Dubai, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.87,0:24:04.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,第一次我去那的时候\N{\fs90}Cos the first time I came here, which was...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.87,0:24:08.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,也就20年前 那还是个小村庄\N{\fs90}was only 20 years ago, it was like a small village.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.51,0:24:10.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,找不到比我更高的东西了\N{\fs90}I was the tallest thing in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.44,0:24:11.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,是吗\N{\fs90}Were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.71,0:24:13.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在看这 不可思议\N{\fs90}Now look at it. It's unbelievable!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.48,0:24:16.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,- 现在可不一样了  - 难以置信\N{\fs90}- It's not that now, is it? - It is unbelievable, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.78,0:24:18.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们知道吗 我身上这件衬衫\N{\fs90}Do you know, this shirt is older
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.48,0:24:20.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,比你们从窗外看到的一切更老\N{\fs90}than everything you can see out of that window.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.72,0:24:23.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 那衬衫比迦太基古城还老 简直不忍直视\N{\fs90}James, that shirt is older than Carthage, mate. Look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.42,0:24:24.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,是有一点\N{\fs90}It is getting on a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.76,0:24:26.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,重点在于\N{\fs90}Anyway, the point I'm trying to make is,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.16,0:24:28.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,我几年前第一次来时\N{\fs90}a few years ago, when I first came here,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.83,0:24:32.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里没有任何交通法规\N{\fs90}there were virtually no motoring laws at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.13,0:24:34.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,有天早上我在旅馆醒来时\N{\fs90}I woke up one morning in my hotel--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.27,0:24:36.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,也是当时唯一的旅馆\N{\fs90}the hotel, there was only one--
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.27,0:24:37.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在那旅馆里回想\N{\fs90}in the hotel, thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.37,0:24:40.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,昨晚我怎么回来的\N{\fs90}"How did I get back here last night?"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.17,0:24:42.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,向窗外看去 两道轮印\N{\fs90}Looked out of the window, two wheel marks
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.34,0:24:45.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,径直穿过景观环岛\N{\fs90}right over the ornamental roundabout.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.38,0:24:48.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我的揽胜停在了花圃里\N{\fs90}And in the flowerbed, my Range Rover.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.61,0:24:52.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,杰里米 你停车时是有多累\N{\fs90}Jeremy, were you very tired when you parked it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.75,0:24:55.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,-眼睛都睁不开了  -好吧\N{\fs90}- I was off my face with tiredness. - OK. OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.76,0:24:58.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,-行  -很难保持清醒\N{\fs90}- OK. - Barely able to concentrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.06,0:25:00.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,当时真的很随便\N{\fs90}But it was an extraordinary free-for-all,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.59,0:25:02.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然现在不一样了\N{\fs90}which I bet it isn't now.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.30,0:25:03.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在已经全然不同了\N{\fs90}It really isn't now.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.53,0:25:05.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在有很多的规则\N{\fs90}There are now very many rules
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.23,0:25:07.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,以及严厉的惩罚 我这有几条\N{\fs90}and many stiff punishments. I've got some of them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.33,0:25:09.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,拖欠汽车贷款\N{\fs90}Getting behind on the repayments on your car loan,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.84,0:25:11.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,会进监狱\N{\fs90}you go to prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.50,0:25:15.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,向其他司机比出粗鲁手势 进监狱\N{\fs90}Making rude gestures at other motorists, you go to prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.08,0:25:16.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,我17岁时\N{\fs90}They're all just the things I did
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.01,0:25:18.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,这些事全干过了\N{\fs90}when I was 17 every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.44,0:25:19.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,我很赞同\N{\fs90}I quite approve of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.78,0:25:21.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,我刚在想 在英国\N{\fs90}I'm just thinking of all the things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.28,0:25:23.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果严格执行的话 哪些行为\N{\fs90}that you could be sent to prison for in Britain
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.78,0:25:25.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,应该被送进监狱\N{\fs90}if we ran it properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.55,0:25:27.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个话题不错 我想到了\N{\fs90}A very good conversation, isn't it? Here's one.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.52,0:25:29.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,那些从加完油上车\N{\fs90}Anyone who takes more than five seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.82,0:25:32.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,到开车走人 花费时间\N{\fs90}between getting in their car after filling up with petrol
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.23,0:25:33.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,超过5秒的人\N{\fs90}and driving off.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.33,0:25:34.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,很有道理\N{\fs90}Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.86,0:25:35.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\fs90}Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.90,0:25:37.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,你懂我的意思吧\N{\fs90}Do you know what I mean by--
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.10,0:25:38.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没错  -在磨蹭啥呢\N{\fs90}- Definitely. - What do they do?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.97,0:25:41.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我又想到一个  -什么\N{\fs90}- I know. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.07,0:25:42.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,用一片木头装菜的\N{\fs90}Restaurant owners who serve food
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.67,0:25:43.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,餐厅老板\N{\fs90}on a piece of wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.97,0:25:45.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,这和车无关吧\N{\fs90}Erm, It's not very car-related,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.37,0:25:47.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不是吗  -是无关 但是\N{\fs90}- is it, really? - No, it's not, but--
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.81,0:25:49.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,赫斯顿 布卢门撒尔就这么干的\N{\fs90}Heston Blumenthal does that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.81,0:25:51.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 他就这么干\N{\fs90}Yes, he does. Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.18,0:25:53.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果赫斯顿你在看节目 小心进监狱哦\N{\fs90}Heston, if you're watching... prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.25,0:25:54.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,蹲号子哦\N{\fs90}You, prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.82,0:25:56.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,我超讨厌用一片木头盛菜\N{\fs90}I hate that-- food on a piece of wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.62,0:25:58.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,告诉你我讨厌什么\N{\fs90}I tell you what I hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.15,0:26:00.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,我可能之前提过几次\N{\fs90}I may have mentioned this a couple of times before.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.12,0:26:01.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,我认为这行为应该判监禁\N{\fs90}And I think it should be imprisonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.92,0:26:04.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,任何允许机舱温度高于20℃的\N{\fs90}Any pilot who allows the cabin of the plane
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.03,0:26:06.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,飞机机长\N{\fs90}to be more than 68°F.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.89,0:26:08.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,-天 又来了  -这点我同意\N{\fs90}- Oh, God. Here we go. - I'm with you on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.86,0:26:11.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,-现在所有飞机都太热了  -没错\N{\fs90}- All planes are too hot these days. - They are.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.83,0:26:14.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,这只是你的例行吐槽\N{\fs90}It's just a standard moan of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.67,0:26:17.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我知道  -天啊\N{\fs90}- I know. I know. - Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.40,0:26:19.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们确实经常一起坐飞机\N{\fs90}We do have to fly together, but I make every effort
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.47,0:26:21.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,每次长途飞行 我都尽量不和大猩猩一起坐\N{\fs90}not to sit near Jeremy Clarkson for a long flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.74,0:26:23.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,但每次\N{\fs90}But eventually, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.08,0:26:24.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,灯一关 眼前一黑\N{\fs90}they turn the lights off and it goes all dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.91,0:26:27.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,10分钟后 黑暗中会响起这个声音\N{\fs90}and after ten minutes this voice over in the blackness goes,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.51,0:26:30.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,"还有比这更热的飞机吗"\N{\fs90}"It's literally the hottest place in the world!"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.92,0:26:34.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,-真的很热  -"我们是要飞向太阳吗\N{\fs90}- It is. - "Are we flying into the sun?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.22,0:26:36.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,温度再高一点 我就要开窗户了"\N{\fs90}If it gets any hotter, I shall open a window!"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.06,0:26:39.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,我听过无数遍了\N{\fs90}I've heard all of this so many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.89,0:26:41.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,讲真 他们为什么要这样\N{\fs90}Honestly, why do they do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.86,0:26:43.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么 这里有飞行员吗\N{\fs90}Why? Are there any pilots here?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.40,0:26:45.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这  -你是飞行员吗\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - You are a pilot?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.73,0:26:47.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,你为什么把温度调那么高\N{\fs90}Why do you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.90,0:26:51.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,你为什么要蒸我们 你哪家公司的\N{\fs90}Why do you boil us all? Who do you fly with?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.24,0:26:52.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,-阿提哈德航空公司  -阿提哈德\N{\fs90}- Etihad. - Etihad.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.87,0:26:54.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你飞机上温度高吗  -很高\N{\fs90}- How hot are the planes? - Very warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.57,0:26:55.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,新规矩\N{\fs90}Well, there's a new rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.78,0:26:57.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,我现在警告你\N{\fs90}I'm telling you. I'm warning you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.34,0:26:59.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,我很严肃的警告你\N{\fs90}I'm seriously warning you on this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.71,0:27:02.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果机舱温度高于20℃ 你一落地\N{\fs90}You land. If it's gone over 68 in the cabin,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.52,0:27:05.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,直接判刑50年\N{\fs90}straight to prison for 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.62,0:27:08.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,我能说一句吗 既然你在这里\N{\fs90}Can I also say, since you're in here--
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.35,0:27:10.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们有点跑题了 -这值得指出\N{\fs90}- We've gone off topic. - It's worth pointing this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.46,0:27:12.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,既然你在这里 当我们都打算睡觉的时候\N{\fs90}Since you're in here, when we're trying to sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.33,0:27:13.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,别告诉我们外面的温度是\N{\fs90}don't tell us the outside temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.99,0:27:15.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,零下57度\N{\fs90}is 57 below zero,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.63,0:27:16.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我们根本不在乎\N{\fs90}cos we don't give a toss.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.00,0:27:18.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,反正你也不能开窗\N{\fs90}Cos you can't open the window anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.60,0:27:20.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们在乎飞机里的温度\N{\fs90}We care about the temperature in the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.04,0:27:23.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,只是一些规矩而已\N{\fs90}Just a few rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.80,0:27:25.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,总之 让我们继续\N{\fs90}Anyway, let's move it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.07,0:27:26.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们能说回到车上吗\N{\fs90}Shall we get back on to some cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.61,0:27:27.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 旅行\N{\fs90}Yeah, travel--
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.97,0:27:29.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,恩 和旅行有关的事情\N{\fs90}Well, sort of travel-related stuff. OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.91,0:27:31.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我这里有张照片\N{\fs90}I've got a photograph here
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.01,0:27:33.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,是英国关于\N{\fs90}of Britain's idea
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.28,0:27:35.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,基础设施建设的点子\N{\fs90}of infrastructure investment, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.25,0:27:37.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,这在剑桥 这是...\N{\fs90}This is in Cambridge. It's erm...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.92,0:27:39.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.39,0:27:41.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是他们设计的T字路口\N{\fs90}It's a T-junction that they've designed,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.62,0:27:43.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,也只有他们自己知道\N{\fs90}for reasons known only to themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.02,0:27:45.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么它这么像环岛\N{\fs90}to look like a roundabout.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.23,0:27:46.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我猜猜看\N{\fs90}Yeah, and let me guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.73,0:27:48.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,这花了一百万吧\N{\fs90}It cost 100 grand to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.66,0:27:50.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 这花了五十万英镑\N{\fs90}No, it was £500,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.56,0:27:52.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,-当然 -五十万英镑\N{\fs90}- Of course it was, yeah. - Half a million pounds
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.57,0:27:54.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们用纳税人的钱就做这个\N{\fs90}they charged the taxpayer for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.30,0:27:56.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,-就用一些瓷砖 -正是\N{\fs90}- For some paving slabs. - Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.17,0:27:59.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管怎样 在迪拜所谓的基础设施\N{\fs90}Anyway, Dubai's idea of infrastructure investment
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.67,0:28:00.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,就有点不一样了\N{\fs90}is a little bit different,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.97,0:28:02.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为他们在计划这个\N{\fs90}cos what they're planning is this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.78,0:28:04.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,这叫超级高铁\N{\fs90}It's called the Hyper Loop.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.81,0:28:06.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,它有点像铁道列车\N{\fs90}It's like a tube train.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.21,0:28:08.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,它将从迪拜开往阿布扎比\N{\fs90}And it'll go from Dubai to Abu Dhabi,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.28,0:28:10.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,差不多有160公里\N{\fs90}which is about 100 miles away,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.02,0:28:13.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,-只需12分钟 -12分钟\N{\fs90}- in 12 minutes. - 12 minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.25,0:28:15.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,12分钟 这就是所需要的时间\N{\fs90}12 minutes. That's how long that will take.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.19,0:28:16.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,它有多快\N{\fs90}So how fast does it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.96,0:28:18.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,每小时800公里\N{\fs90}500 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.39,0:28:22.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,这实在是太惊人了 真的\N{\fs90}I mean, that is just breath-taking. It really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.30,0:28:24.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你刚刚是说有160公里吗 -是的\N{\fs90}- Did you say it was 100 miles? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.60,0:28:27.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,它能以800公里的时速在12分钟内走160公里\N{\fs90}It's going 100 miles at 500mph in 12 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.23,0:28:30.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,这意味着它可以瞬间加速至800kph\N{\fs90}That means it accelerates to 500mph instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.54,0:28:32.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,-嗯 -在里面推辆饮料小推车\N{\fs90}- Mm. - You're gonna have trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.17,0:28:33.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,你会出事的\N{\fs90}holding on to the drinks trolley in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.38,0:28:37.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,当它启动的时候 你会拉裤子\N{\fs90}When it sets off, you'll poo yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.98,0:28:39.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后当它停下来\N{\fs90}Then, when it stops,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.25,0:28:41.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,你又会尿自己一身\N{\fs90}you'll wee yourself at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.45,0:28:43.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里 这里有医生吗\N{\fs90}It's a... Are there any doctors here?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.22,0:28:45.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,我只是说说 这可不是什么医疗纠纷\N{\fs90}I'm just saying. It's not a medical argument.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.12,0:28:46.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我只是说说 -我不确定你对不对\N{\fs90}- I'm just saying. - I'm not sure you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.99,0:28:48.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 想想牛顿\N{\fs90}Well, think about Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.72,0:28:50.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,当它起步加速时 你会拉裤子\N{\fs90}If you set off, you'll poo yourself, yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.59,0:28:52.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是当它减速的时候 你会反向拉裤子\N{\fs90}but when it slows down, you'll un-poo yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.56,0:28:56.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为万物都会受到等大的反向作用力\N{\fs90}because everything has an equal and opposite reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.53,0:28:59.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说的没错吧 这里有物理学家吗\N{\fs90}I'm roughly right, aren't I? Any physicists here?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.53,0:29:01.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我觉得我们该继续了 -是的\N{\fs90}- I think we should move on. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.14,0:29:04.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这一季开头\N{\fs90}Right at the beginning of the series,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.77,0:29:06.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德和我提出了\N{\fs90}Richard Hammond and I came up
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.41,0:29:08.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,一个绝妙的主意叫做\N{\fs90}with a rather brilliant idea called...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.68,0:29:11.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,让船长\N{\fs90}...Making James May
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.28,0:29:13.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,做他不想做的事情\N{\fs90}Do Things He Doesn't Want To Do.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.55,0:29:16.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 偶然情况下的好点子\N{\fs90}Yep. A brilliant idea for an occasional feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.75,0:29:19.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们让他去南非参加了一个甜甜圈节\N{\fs90}We made him go to a doughnuting festival in South Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.92,0:29:21.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的 -他很讨厌这个\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - He hated it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.62,0:29:24.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后他觉得我们把这忘了\N{\fs90}Then he thought we'd forgotten about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.69,0:29:26.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是我们并没有\N{\fs90}But we hadn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.73,0:29:29.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里就是那种\N{\fs90}This is the sort of countryside
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.50,0:29:31.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,人们可以享受美好事物的郊外\N{\fs90}where people can do nice things,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.73,0:29:34.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,比如散散步或者野餐\N{\fs90}like go for a walk or a picnic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.80,0:29:37.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而这里 是那种\N{\fs90}This, however, is the sort of countryside
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.57,0:29:40.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,会成为我今天归属的郊外—泥巴\N{\fs90}that will be my home for the day-- mud.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.54,0:29:42.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 我喜欢泥巴\N{\fs90}Yes, I love mud.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.44,0:29:46.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,当我说我爱泥巴的时候 其实在说我恨它\N{\fs90}When I say I love mud, I mean I hate mud.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.61,0:29:50.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是今天 跟我一起的人都喜欢\N{\fs90}But the people with me here today really do love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.35,0:29:52.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们梦寐以求\N{\fs90}They dream of the stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.75,0:29:55.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我身后的这些人叫做绞盘党\N{\fs90}These people behind me are called winchers,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.86,0:29:57.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们喜欢做的事情就是拉绞盘\N{\fs90}and what they like doing is winching.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.06,0:30:00.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们会故意\N{\fs90}They will drive, deliberately,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.86,0:30:03.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,开进像那里的泥坑\N{\fs90}into something like that puddle over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.80,0:30:08.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,直到陷进去 然后再用绞盘拉出来\N{\fs90}..until they get stuck, and then winch themselves out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.57,0:30:11.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,做完以后 他们会找另一处\N{\fs90}When they've done that, they'll find another one...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.74,0:30:14.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,像这样循环往复\N{\fs90}and do it again, and again,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.37,0:30:16.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,折腾一整天\N{\fs90}and again, and again, all day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.05,0:30:20.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,绞盘党们看起来痴迷于\N{\fs90}Winchers seem to be obsessed
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.95,0:30:24.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,让日子尽可能的艰难\N{\fs90}with making life as difficult as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.25,0:30:26.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们将定向越野标记点\N{\fs90}They put orienteering punches
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.15,0:30:28.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,放在几乎不可能的位置\N{\fs90}in almost unreachable locations...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.89,0:30:32.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后试图把他们的4x4s开到那里\N{\fs90}and then try to get their 4x4s right up to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.93,0:30:38.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢默斯道尔 我今天的绞盘兄弟解释道\N{\fs90}as Seamus Doyle, my winch buddy for the day, explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.10,0:30:39.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,有50个标记点\N{\fs90}There are 50 punches
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.53,0:30:41.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,遍布这个场所的不同地方\N{\fs90}dotted around in different parts of the site.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.43,0:30:43.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,在车边有一张打孔卡\N{\fs90}We have a punch card on the side of the vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.74,0:30:46.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,你要用它够到标记点\N{\fs90}You've got to get this punchcard to the punch.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.54,0:30:48.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,这些标记点会拴在绳子上\N{\fs90}The punch will be on a string
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.11,0:30:49.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,有可能离树两尺远 或者一尺\N{\fs90}maybe 2ft long from the tree, or maybe 1ft.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.01,0:30:51.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以你就可以在数字上打卡\N{\fs90}So you've got to punch the number.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.41,0:30:52.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,-就像打孔机 -是的\N{\fs90}- Like a hole puncher? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.78,0:30:54.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,当你卡住的时候\N{\fs90}When you get stuck,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.28,0:30:56.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为你会卡主\N{\fs90}because you're gonna get stuck...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.15,0:30:57.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的 -我得逃出来\N{\fs90}- Yes. Yeah, yeah. - I have to get out
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.65,0:30:59.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后把绞盘挂在树上\N{\fs90}and attach the winch to a tree?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.25,0:31:00.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 你得出来\N{\fs90}Yes, you'll get out,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.59,0:31:02.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,你得带着你的皮带\N{\fs90}and you'll get your strap with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.29,0:31:04.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,用皮带包着可以保护树\N{\fs90}The strap goes round the tree to protect the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.22,0:31:05.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后你再把你的绞盘挂在树上\N{\fs90}Then you bring your wincher up to the tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.13,0:31:07.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者随便什么东西\N{\fs90}or whatever obstacle we attach it to,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.13,0:31:09.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,我会操作那些按钮\N{\fs90}and I'll operate the buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.90,0:31:11.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你的英语很好  -谢谢\N{\fs90}- Your English is excellent. - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.50,0:31:13.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,我练习了很久了\N{\fs90}I've been practising for a long time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.13,0:31:14.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,在上面花了很多力气\N{\fs90}A lot of practice has gone into that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.50,0:31:19.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,比赛一开始\N{\fs90}As soon as the contest began,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.51,0:31:22.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢默斯指明了 我人生中的新角色\N{\fs90}Seamus made it plain that my new role in life
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.14,0:31:24.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是做他的绞盘婊\N{\fs90}was to be his winch bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.18,0:31:30.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,走啊 走走走\N{\fs90}OK, got to go, go, go.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.55,0:31:32.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,-什么 我要走出去 -是的\N{\fs90}- What, I've got to get out? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.15,0:31:34.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,你觉得我还可以往哪走\N{\fs90}Where the hell do you think I'm gonna go?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.15,0:31:36.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,拿着绞车缆索到那棵树那里\N{\fs90}Go with the winch rope to that tree over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.16,0:31:38.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦伙计啊\N{\fs90}Oh, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.32,0:31:39.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,这感觉有点像...\N{\fs90}This is like being a...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.49,0:31:42.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,他妈的河马\N{\fs90}(BLEEP) hippopotamus.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.93,0:31:47.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,时间紧迫\N{\fs90}OK, the clock is ticking.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.93,0:31:49.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,在拿到了我们第一个标记点之后\N{\fs90}Having got our first punch,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.57,0:31:53.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,我希望今天能过得稍微好一点\N{\fs90}I was hoping the day might get a bit less terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.07,0:31:54.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是并没有\N{\fs90}But it didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.71,0:32:00.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,-哦天 -詹姆斯 给力啊\N{\fs90}- Oh, man! - James, come on, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.05,0:32:06.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在绞我自己\N{\fs90}I'm winching myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.49,0:32:07.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,这样好多了\N{\fs90}Oh, that's much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.62,0:32:08.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 我说这"好多了"\N{\fs90}Well, I say it's "much better",
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.05,0:32:10.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,其实是少点操蛋\N{\fs90}it's less shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.36,0:32:13.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,走 我们要弥补时间\N{\fs90}Go! We've got to make up time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.06,0:32:15.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我有个好点子 -什么\N{\fs90}- I've got a great idea. - Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.93,0:32:19.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,-为什么不是你出来打卡 -不要\N{\fs90}- Why don't you get out and get the punch? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.06,0:32:20.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么我一直要干这个\N{\fs90}Why do I have to keep doing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.60,0:32:22.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要做司机 那样行不通\N{\fs90}Me being the driver, it doesn't work that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.71,0:32:27.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 我们接下来去哪儿郊游啊\N{\fs90}Right, where next on our lovely Sunday drive?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.51,0:32:32.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们要下去 -别傻了\N{\fs90}- We're going down here. - Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.71,0:32:37.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们又卡住了\N{\fs90}- We're stuck again.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.25,0:32:38.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,出去绞起来 伙计\N{\fs90}Get the winch out here, buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.82,0:32:41.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,看到那里的树了吗\N{\fs90}See the tree over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.89,0:32:43.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个全他妈的是树\N{\fs90}The place is full of (BLEEP) trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.96,0:32:45.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,太糟糕了\N{\fs90}This is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.46,0:32:47.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的神啊\N{\fs90}Christ!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.73,0:32:51.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,在一些偶然的情况下\N{\fs90}On the odd occasion when I did manage
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.53,0:32:53.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我即使能坐在车里\N{\fs90}a sit-down in the car,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.27,0:32:55.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢默斯也要添乱\N{\fs90}Seamus even managed to ruin that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.24,0:33:01.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,这压根没必要\N{\fs90}That wasn't even necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.51,0:33:03.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,你只是想惹怒我\N{\fs90}You just did that to piss me off.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.81,0:33:05.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,不不不\N{\fs90}No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.25,0:33:11.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们快做到了 船长\N{\fs90}We nearly made it, James.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.75,0:33:14.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 但是你没做到 我可以回家了吗\N{\fs90}Yeah, but you didn't. Now can I go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.25,0:33:16.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,在那个山丘上打地锚\N{\fs90}Ground anchor over the hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.89,0:33:22.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你就坐那儿对吧 -我不走 放心\N{\fs90}- You just sit there, OK? - I'll be here, OK, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.43,0:33:24.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们在这里四个小时了\N{\fs90}It's four hours we've been in here now,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.36,0:33:25.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而我们实际的行进距离...\N{\fs90}and we've travelled, in reality...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.17,0:33:29.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,只有150米\N{\fs90}...150 metres.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.77,0:33:32.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,今天要是能做任何其他事\N{\fs90}All the things I could be doing today
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.31,0:33:34.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,我都愿意做\N{\fs90}that I would rather do,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.37,0:33:36.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,包括自残\N{\fs90}which include self-harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.65,0:33:43.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,不幸中的万幸 比赛总算要结束了\N{\fs90}Mercifully, the contest eventually came to an end,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.02,0:33:47.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们也终于回程参加颁奖礼\N{\fs90}and we were finally on our way back to prize-giving.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.02,0:33:51.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好消息是我们不是最后一名 -你怎么知道的\N{\fs90}- The good news is we're not gonna come last. - How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.09,0:33:53.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为十点的时候有个男孩车坏了\N{\fs90}Because one of the boys broke down since ten o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.86,0:33:54.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,他真他妈走运\N{\fs90}Lucky bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.93,0:33:56.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦天呐\N{\fs90}Oh, geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.30,0:33:57.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,我上去了上去了\N{\fs90}I'm on it. I'm on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.73,0:33:59.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 你过头了\N{\fs90}No, you're gonna overdo it!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.43,0:34:02.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 这可以的 没事的\N{\fs90}-No, it's OK. You're OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.44,0:34:04.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你个白痴 -都怪你\N{\fs90}-You idiot! - Your fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.44,0:34:07.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,是你在开车 傻子\N{\fs90}It was you driving, you fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.14,0:34:09.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,这下面好臭\N{\fs90}It stinks down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.14,0:34:11.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,神呐 这是什么玩意儿\N{\fs90}God! What is this stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.31,0:34:13.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,英国大陆\N{\fs90}England.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.31,0:34:16.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,最终 我们还是赶上了颁奖\N{\fs90}At last, we made it back for the prize-giving.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.49,0:34:21.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以 快速总结一下\N{\fs90}So, here's a quick sum-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.45,0:34:23.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,在经历了7个小时之后\N{\fs90}Er... At the end of a seven-hour day,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.66,0:34:27.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,我被卡了50余次\N{\fs90}I've... been stuck 50-something times.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.93,0:34:29.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,我摔了有\N{\fs90}Erm... I've fallen over,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.76,0:34:32.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,我也没数 差不多25次\N{\fs90}I haven't actually been counting, something like 25 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.93,0:34:35.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,我差点在三个泥坑里淹死\N{\fs90}I've nearly drowned in three puddles.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.40,0:34:37.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果我可以赢一个绞盘或者绞盘套\N{\fs90}And that wouldn't be so bad
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.44,0:34:39.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,可能还不算太糟\N{\fs90}if I was gonna win a winch or a winch cover
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.41,0:34:41.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者赢一卷新绳之类的\N{\fs90}or a new piece of rope or something like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.34,0:34:42.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是 事实截然相反\N{\fs90}but, in fact, in the rollover,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.88,0:34:45.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们的打孔卡掉下来了 从严格意义上说\N{\fs90}we tore the punchcard off, which means, technically,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.68,0:34:48.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们得从头开始比赛\N{\fs90}we've got to start again from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.81,0:34:51.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是我宁可把去把自己淹死\N{\fs90}But I've decided to go and drown myself instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.36,0:34:57.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我很喜欢谢默斯 -是的 我喜欢他\N{\fs90}- I like Seamus a lot. - Yeah, I like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.36,0:34:59.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,-谢默斯是我新的好朋友 -这当然啦\N{\fs90}- Seamus is my new best friend. - Yeah, definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.99,0:35:02.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,-毁了船长 -我们还要来更多这样的\N{\fs90}- Ruined James May. - We need to do a lot more of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.36,0:35:04.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的 更多 -非常多\N{\fs90}- Yeah, a lot more. A lot more. - Many more.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.83,0:35:08.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以 船长 有任何你喜欢的地方吗\N{\fs90}So, James, was there any aspect of that that you liked?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.87,0:35:10.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没有 -很好\N{\fs90}- No. - Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.14,0:35:12.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,继续 现在是时候\N{\fs90}So, moving on, it's time now
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.10,0:35:14.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,进入明星脑碰脑\N{\fs90}to play Celebrity Brain Crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.95,0:35:23.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这丝毫没有进步 -是没有\N{\fs90}- That doesn't get any better. - It doesn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.95,0:35:26.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,总之 我们今天的嘉宾\N{\fs90}Anyway, our guest today
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.79,0:35:31.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,是一级方程式赛车里闪亮的新星\N{\fs90}is a shining star from the world of Formula One.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.26,0:35:32.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,他也是一个很有勇气的年轻人\N{\fs90}He's also a very brave young man,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.79,0:35:35.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为 即使他充分了解到\N{\fs90}because, even though he is fully aware
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.29,0:35:36.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,之前发生在\N{\fs90}of all of the calamities
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.73,0:35:38.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,其他名人身上 在试图来帐篷时\N{\fs90}that have befallen all the other celebrities
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.56,0:35:40.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,发生的惨案\N{\fs90}that have tried to come to our tent,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.80,0:35:44.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,他还是选择坐气垫船来\N{\fs90}he's elected to arrive in a hovercraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.94,0:35:47.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们 丹尼尔·里卡多\N{\fs90}Ladies and gentlemen, Daniel Ricciardo!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.68,0:35:51.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他来了 -他来了\N{\fs90}-And there he is. -There he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.78,0:35:53.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,戴上他的头盔\N{\fs90}Putting his helmet on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.45,0:35:55.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得 这是明智的举动\N{\fs90}That's a wise move, I think. A wise move.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.82,0:35:59.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,我真的真的很喜欢丹尼尔·里卡多\N{\fs90}I genuinely, genuinely like Daniel Ricciardo,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.62,0:36:02.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为他真的是一个很好的人\N{\fs90}because he is a truly nice man.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.29,0:36:03.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,他是个好人\N{\fs90}He's a truly nice man,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.69,0:36:05.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,他还非常开心和愉快\N{\fs90}and he's also extremely happy and cheerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.76,0:36:07.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,只是 以我的个人经验\N{\fs90}I just... Well, I know from personal experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.03,0:36:09.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,气垫船很难控制\N{\fs90}hovercrafts are tricky to control.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.03,0:36:12.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,杰里米 他可是一个F1车手\N{\fs90}Yeah, Jeremy, he's a Formula One driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.60,0:36:14.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他能做到的 -可是风很大\N{\fs90}- He's got this covered. - No, but it's windy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.90,0:36:17.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦他来了 他来了 到了\N{\fs90}Oh, here he comes. Here he is, arriving now.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.27,0:36:20.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他做的很好 -操控得很好\N{\fs90}- He's fine with that. - Wrestling with the controls and doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.34,0:36:21.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的 -噢他开过了\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - Oh, he's overshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.74,0:36:24.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,他是有点开过了 哦天哪\N{\fs90}He's overshot a bit there. Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.01,0:36:27.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦不\N{\fs90}Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.58,0:36:29.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦那就是说...他来不了了\N{\fs90}Oh, there's been... No, there's been a... No.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.55,0:36:32.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,我去 他卷到风扇里了 风扇啊\N{\fs90}Oh, God! He's going in the fan! He's going in the fan!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.69,0:36:34.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦不\N{\fs90}Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.59,0:36:37.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,这...\N{\fs90}Oh, that...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.50,0:36:47.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,看那头盔\N{\fs90}The helmet...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.83,0:36:51.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,还好头盔和他的头一起卡住了马达\N{\fs90}The helmet has now thankfully jammed the motor with his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.24,0:36:52.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 太迟了\N{\fs90}Yeah, it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.48,0:36:59.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以是不是说 他来不了了\N{\fs90}Does that mean he's not coming on, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.14,0:37:02.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,听着船长 他被榨了汁 而且布满窗户\N{\fs90}Well, James, he's been liquidised and now he's all over the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.28,0:37:03.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以他来不了了\N{\fs90}so, no, he's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.93,0:37:05.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,与其说在帐篷里 不如说在帐篷上\N{\fs90}Yeah, he's not in the tent so much as on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.84,0:37:07.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的...\N{\fs90}Yeah. Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.04,0:37:10.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们接下来干嘛 -总得做点什么\N{\fs90}- What do we do next? - We've got to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.81,0:37:13.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 你不介意的话 我去把它擦干净\N{\fs90}Well, I'm gonna clean that off, if you don't mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.14,0:37:15.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,太让人分心了 还很恶心\N{\fs90}It is distracting and off-putting.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.11,0:37:16.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们怎么打发时间\N{\fs90}How do we fill the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.58,0:37:17.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,没事 我早就预见到\N{\fs90}It's all right, because I thought
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.91,0:37:19.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,会发生这种事\N{\fs90}something like this might happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.65,0:37:20.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们抵达之后\N{\fs90}So when we arrived last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.95,0:37:22.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,我出门拍了一小段视频\N{\fs90}I went out and I made a little film.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.85,0:37:24.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢天谢地 什么视频\N{\fs90}Thank God for that. What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.62,0:37:26.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好的 让我们... -我们把它遮起来\N{\fs90}- Well, let's just... - We'll cover this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.22,0:37:28.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想告诉你们\N{\fs90}I'd like to talk to you now--
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.92,0:37:30.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不 我们得拉近镜头 -好主意\N{\fs90}- No, we need to tighten the shot. - Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.06,0:37:34.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,镜头对准他 就拍脸\N{\fs90}Tighten it on him. Just our faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.06,0:37:36.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,注意力集中在我\N{\fs90}Concentrate on me and what I'm saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.40,0:37:37.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有我说的话上\N{\fs90}and not on anything else
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.70,0:37:39.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,不要看其他的东西\N{\fs90}that you might be tempted to look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.57,0:37:41.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 保时捷918\N{\fs90}Erm... Now, the Porsche 918,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.57,0:37:44.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,之前的节目中我们证明了\N{\fs90}earlier in this series of programmes we saw it in action
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.91,0:37:46.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,它是三大神车中\N{\fs90}and proved that it is the ultimate
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.64,0:37:49.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,最后的王者\N{\fs90}of the hypercar Holy Trinity
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.11,0:37:51.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们拿它和法拉利 迈凯伦做对比\N{\fs90}when we put it against the Ferrari and the McLaren.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.35,0:37:52.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我总是想\N{\fs90}But I've always wondered,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.65,0:37:54.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,"如果我们跑直线的话\N{\fs90}"How would it fare in a straight race
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.32,0:37:55.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,它和布加迪威龙谁快"\N{\fs90}against a Bugatti Veyron?"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.75,0:37:58.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在我们在超级跑车之乡\N{\fs90}And as we are in the home of the hypercar,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.59,0:38:00.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,应该在这儿一探究竟\N{\fs90}this is the place to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.16,0:38:02.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,好 对准我 怎么样 好的\N{\fs90}Yeah. Now, tight on me. Are we tight? Good. Erm...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.86,0:38:04.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是...\N{\fs90}This is, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.19,0:38:05.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是一场竞速\N{\fs90}This is a... It's a race
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.76,0:38:07.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,过去和未来之间的对决\N{\fs90}between the future and the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.90,0:38:09.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,今晚的第二次了\N{\fs90}Second time this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.43,0:38:10.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 和你的片子很像\N{\fs90}Yeah, much like your film,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.73,0:38:12.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这次是激动人心的\N{\fs90}only this one is exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.66,0:38:34.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 终于\N{\fs90}So, here we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.86,0:38:36.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,昔日的性能王者\N{\fs90}The grand old man of performance
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.29,0:38:38.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,再次出山 捍卫正名\N{\fs90}coming out one more time to defend his title
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.76,0:38:40.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,和后起之秀同台竞技\N{\fs90}against one of the young upstarts.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.70,0:38:42.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,纸面数据如下\N{\fs90}Here's how it all pans out on paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.63,0:38:45.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,布加迪威龙:百公里加速2.5秒\N{\fs90}Bugatti Veyron: 0-60, 2.5 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.94,0:38:47.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,功率质量比:\N{\fs90}Power-to-weight ratio:
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.47,0:38:50.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,每吨523马力\N{\fs90}523 brake horsepower per tonne.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.44,0:38:53.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,保时捷918:百公里加速2.6秒\N{\fs90}The 918: 0-60, 2.6 seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.94,0:38:55.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是功率质量比为\N{\fs90}but a power-to-weight ratio
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.18,0:38:58.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,每吨535马力\N{\fs90}of 535 brake horsepower per tonne.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.78,0:39:01.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而 在第一期节目中\N{\fs90}However, as we learned when we raced the 918
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.55,0:39:04.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们驾驶918对抗拉法和P1\N{\fs90}against the LaFerrari and the P1 in our first show,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.45,0:39:07.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,这种指标完全没用\N{\fs90}hard facts like that count for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.79,0:39:09.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,最终看的还是这个\N{\fs90}In the end, it's all down to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.56,0:39:15.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,我准备好比赛了\N{\fs90}And I'm ready to race.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.27,0:39:19.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,其实...\N{\fs90}Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.40,0:39:22.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,爽\N{\fs90}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.98,0:39:31.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,最后一点死皮\N{\fs90}Last bit of dead skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.09,0:39:39.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 弹射起步:赛道模式\N{\fs90}OK. Launch control: race mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.56,0:39:44.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,这儿代表着未来\N{\fs90}Representing the future here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.78,0:40:07.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想...只要我保持领先\N{\fs90}I think... if I can just stay ahead...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.49,0:40:13.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,太接近了\N{\fs90}This is going to be so close!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.99,0:40:17.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,未来要获胜了\N{\fs90}The future is gonna take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.73,0:40:23.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,抱歉 威龙 但是你的皇冠不再\N{\fs90}So sorry, Veyron, but your crown is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.13,0:40:24.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,哇喔\N{\fs90}Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.70,0:40:27.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,多好的车啊\N{\fs90}What a device this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.54,0:40:32.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,显然 我打算就这么收尾了\N{\fs90}I was gonna call it a day at that, obviously,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.98,0:40:36.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这儿有个家伙想拿日产比一比\N{\fs90}but there's a bloke here wants to race his Nissan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.65,0:40:39.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,实在是有点丢人\N{\fs90}It's a bit embarrassing, really,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.05,0:40:41.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,但你总不能惹毛当地人\N{\fs90}but you don't want to upset the locals.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.82,0:40:44.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以比赛吧 我们走\N{\fs90}So, OK, race is on. Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.82,0:40:50.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们速战速决\N{\fs90}Let's get this over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.13,0:40:52.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,跑比赛 说抱歉 然后过\N{\fs90}Do race, apologise, move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.81,0:41:03.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,什么\N{\fs90}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.41,0:41:08.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,他居然用日产途乐甩开我了\N{\fs90}He's pulling away in a Nissan Patrol!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.42,0:41:22.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,到底 发生了 什么\N{\fs90}What... just... happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.90,0:41:32.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,等一下\N{\fs90}So, hang on a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.24,0:41:34.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这一季的开头\N{\fs90}At the beginning of this series,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.04,0:41:38.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们把那三辆超跑神车\N{\fs90}we bigged up the hypercar Holy Trinity
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.57,0:41:40.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,吹成了有史以来\N{\fs90}as the three greatest cars
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.08,0:41:42.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,构思和发明过的最好的车\N{\fs90}ever to have been conceived and invented.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.68,0:41:44.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的 -而它们之中最快的...\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - And the fastest of all of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.05,0:41:48.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,-嗯 -...被一辆日产面包车吊打\N{\fs90}- Yes. - ...was beaten by a Datsun van.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.82,0:41:51.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fs90}Yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.42,0:41:53.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,它用的什么鬼引擎\N{\fs90}What the hell engine did it have?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.16,0:41:57.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,事实上它有1900匹马力\N{\fs90}Well, it turns out it's got 1,900 horsepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.29,0:41:59.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,-保时捷想什么呢 -就是说\N{\fs90}- What were Porsche thinking of? - I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.83,0:42:01.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,回炉重造吧 伙计们\N{\fs90}Back to the drawing boards, lads,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.26,0:42:03.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们先遮着点 -很好\N{\fs90}- and we'll gloss over that. - Exactly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.33,0:42:06.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,你太丢人了 保时捷\N{\fs90}Your embarrassing mistake, Porsche.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.34,0:42:08.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在 我想坦白说 实际上\N{\fs90}Now, I'd like to make a confession, actually, and it's this.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.94,0:42:13.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,我一直不会真正的漂移\N{\fs90}I've never been able to drift properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.38,0:42:15.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,这实在是....别管他\N{\fs90}It's just... I know, just ignore him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.64,0:42:17.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,没什么好看的\N{\fs90}Nothing to see. Nothing to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.45,0:42:18.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,这儿没东西可看\N{\fs90}Nothing to see here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.75,0:42:20.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,只是一个男人在做他的工作\N{\fs90}It's just a man doing his job.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.35,0:42:23.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,我一直不会正确地漂移\N{\fs90}I've never been able to drift properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.85,0:42:25.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,我能引发车的侧滑\N{\fs90}I can provoke a car, you know, into a slide,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.06,0:42:27.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是我没法控制住\N{\fs90}but I couldn't hold it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.39,0:42:28.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,总是原地打转 或者撞车\N{\fs90}It would always just spin off and crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.96,0:42:30.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,正是 我想说\N{\fs90}No, exactly. I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.63,0:42:32.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们以前看到他做的漂移\N{\fs90}everything you've ever seen in the past of him drifting
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.53,0:42:35.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,都是使用烟雾 镜子 神剪辑\N{\fs90}has been done with smoke, mirrors, clever editing
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.36,0:42:37.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,老实说 还有特技车手\N{\fs90}and, let's be honest, stunt drivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.57,0:42:40.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以当我们开始录制Grand Tour的时候\N{\fs90}So I decided when we started making Grand Tour
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.27,0:42:41.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,我决定改变这一现状\N{\fs90}that I had to go out and change that,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.04,0:42:44.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,并学会如何正确地漂移\N{\fs90}and learn how to do it properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.25,0:42:51.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,有一种选项\N{\fs90}One option would be to go
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.88,0:42:54.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是周六晚上去超市的停车场\N{\fs90}to a supermarket car park on a Saturday night,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.92,0:42:57.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我来到了法国\N{\fs90}but instead I came here to France.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.39,0:43:05.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,准确地说 到了高度机密的\N{\fs90}Specifically, to the top-secret
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.49,0:43:07.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,拉度测试中心\N{\fs90}Ladoux test centre,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.13,0:43:09.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,米其林在这里研发轮胎\N{\fs90}where Michelin develops its tyres.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.00,0:43:15.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,我来这里有几个原因\N{\fs90}There are several reasons why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.07,0:43:16.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,首先 他们有场地\N{\fs90}First, they have the space.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.11,0:43:23.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,43公里的测试跑道和定圆漂移场\N{\fs90}Twenty-seven miles of test tracks and skid pans.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.35,0:43:28.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,其次 如果你想了解漂移\N{\fs90}Second, if you want to understand drifting,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.92,0:43:30.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,你得了解轮胎\N{\fs90}you have to understand tyres,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.92,0:43:33.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,而这里正是轮胎圣殿\N{\fs90}and this place is a tyre temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.16,0:43:44.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,第三 也是最重要的\N{\fs90}Third, and most important,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.20,0:43:46.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,你想要了解轮胎\N{\fs90}if you want to know about tyres,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.67,0:43:48.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,你就得知道如何漂移\N{\fs90}you have to know how to drift,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.47,0:43:51.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,那就是这位老兄的专长\N{\fs90}and that is where this chap comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.15,0:43:58.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,他叫杰罗姆·哈斯林\N{\fs90}His name is Jérôme Haslin,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.58,0:44:01.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,他是米其林的首席轮胎测试员\N{\fs90}and he is Michelin's chief tyre tester
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.28,0:44:04.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,专为宝马 保时捷 法拉利和布加迪做测试\N{\fs90}for BMW, Porsche, Ferrari and Bugatti.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.12,0:44:08.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,橡胶在血管中涌动\N{\fs90}Rubber compound runs through his veins.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.32,0:44:10.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,他是抓地力的一代宗师\N{\fs90}He is a Zen master of grip,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.63,0:44:12.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,漂移界的功夫熊猫\N{\fs90}a Kung Fu Panda of drifting,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.79,0:44:15.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我是他的小学生\N{\fs90}and I am to be his new pupil.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.35,0:44:41.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是他所谓的"超越极限"\N{\fs90}This is what he means by "over the limit".
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.59,0:44:44.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,他用动力把车尾甩出线外\N{\fs90}He uses power to kick the back of the car out of line...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.03,0:44:48.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后通过精准的油门和转向\N{\fs90}and then a delicate balance of throttle and steering
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.60,0:44:50.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,来保持漂移\N{\fs90}to keep it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.27,0:44:54.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,你打方向的技巧真是绝了\N{\fs90}Your steering-wheel technique is amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.87,0:44:57.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,我总是和油门踏板嬉戏\N{\fs90}I play a lot with the gas pedal.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.54,0:45:03.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你踩油门熟练了\N{\fs90}And if you work a lot with the gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.35,0:45:05.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,你就不需要控制方向盘了\N{\fs90}you have nothing to do with the steering.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.31,0:45:07.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,就可以单手漂移 就像这样\N{\fs90}You can do all with one hand, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.72,0:45:11.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,-所以你在用右脚转向吗 -是的\N{\fs90}- So you're steering the car with your right foot? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.36,0:45:16.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,杰罗姆 我学这个太明智了\N{\fs90}Jérôme, this is brilliant that I learn how to do this
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.46,0:45:18.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为你看到网上的那种\N{\fs90}because you read those lists on the Internet
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.83,0:45:21.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,女人欣赏男人的清单 看到过吗\N{\fs90}of things that women appreciate in a man, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.63,0:45:24.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,里面总会有诚实 正直\N{\fs90}And there's always honesty, integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.43,0:45:26.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,忠诚 忠贞 漂移之类的\N{\fs90}loyalty, fidelity, drifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.80,0:45:28.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,总是必要的\N{\fs90}It's always there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.80,0:45:33.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,到了我学习的时候了\N{\fs90}On that note, it was time for me to begin my lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.38,0:45:35.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,你可以把座椅再调调\N{\fs90}You can pull up the seat more.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.05,0:45:38.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,-怎么调 -更靠近方向盘一点\N{\fs90}- More what? - More close to the steering wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.25,0:45:39.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,你什么意思\N{\fs90}What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.85,0:45:44.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 那我开始了\N{\fs90}OK. So, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.69,0:45:48.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,制造转向过度 漂起来了 然后给\N{\fs90}Provoking oversteer, coming off, and then feeding...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.19,0:45:50.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 这成了原地打转了\N{\fs90}No, and then going round in a small circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.73,0:45:56.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的挑战是漂完整的一圈\N{\fs90}My challenge was to drift the car for one complete lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.80,0:45:59.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,给油 多打方向\N{\fs90}Gas, oversteer.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.60,0:46:02.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,-松油门 反打方向 -松油门 反打方向\N{\fs90}- Release gas, counter-steer. - Release gas, counter-steer.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.70,0:46:04.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,-噢我原地打转了 -没事\N{\fs90}- Oh, I've spun! - OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.94,0:46:07.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,给油 给油 给油\N{\fs90}Gas, gas, gas, gas!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.74,0:46:09.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 妈蛋\N{\fs90}Oh, bugger!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.08,0:46:13.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,没多久 不停的原地打转\N{\fs90}Soon, the constant spinning
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.85,0:46:16.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,就开始让我的老师产生了不良反应\N{\fs90}started to have an effect on my teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.79,0:46:20.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,再给一点油 不\N{\fs90}A little bit more power. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.96,0:46:23.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,对 松开油门\N{\fs90}Yeah, off the gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.66,0:46:29.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,奇怪了 我还以为这很简单的\N{\fs90}This is weird. I thought this would be so easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.37,0:46:36.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好的 能让我呼吸下新鲜空气吗 -当然\N{\fs90}- OK, is it possible to take air? Fresh air? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.14,0:46:38.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,-因为我马上就要吐了\N{\fs90}Because I will be ill in two minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.01,0:46:41.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,我做的很不好吗\N{\fs90}Is this going badly?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.11,0:46:48.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,当杰罗姆去和他吃过的早饭说拜拜的时候\N{\fs90}While Jérôme went off to say hello to his breakfast...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.02,0:46:54.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,我继续埋头苦练\N{\fs90}I continued plugging away.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.72,0:46:56.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,快速地给油并反打方向\N{\fs90}Begin power and begin counter-steer immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.86,0:46:58.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后保持住\N{\fs90}Now hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.60,0:47:03.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,没多久就开始有了好的苗头\N{\fs90}And soon, it started to click.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.60,0:47:09.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,老子现在绝对是在漂移 无可辩驳\N{\fs90}What I am doing is drifting. There's no denying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.21,0:47:12.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 就是这样\N{\fs90}Oh, yes! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.87,0:47:15.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的脚已经和方向盘融为一体了\N{\fs90}I've connected the steering wheel to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.48,0:47:18.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是一种全新的体验\N{\fs90}This is a whole new feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.15,0:47:20.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是我去应付侧滑\N{\fs90}This is not reacting to a slide,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.15,0:47:22.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,而是故意引起侧滑\N{\fs90}this is deliberately provoking it
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.65,0:47:24.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后保持在这个状态上\N{\fs90}and keeping it right on the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.96,0:47:31.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈哈 杰罗姆 你这法国的...(模仿法国口音)\N{\fs90}Ha-ha, Jérôme, you French...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.56,0:47:34.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,指导漂移和滑雪的家伙\N{\fs90}drift-and-ski-instructing dude, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.16,0:47:35.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,他会刮目相看的\N{\fs90}He'll be impressed with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.90,0:47:38.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,的确\N{\fs90}And he was,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.17,0:47:39.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们很快进入了\N{\fs90}so we immediately progressed
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.00,0:47:42.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,下一个阶段\N{\fs90}to the next level.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.57,0:47:44.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,杰罗姆 在我们开始前\N{\fs90}Just before we start, Jérôme,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.17,0:47:47.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,你真的要让这看起来简单到爆吗\N{\fs90}are you going to make this look really annoyingly easy?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.21,0:47:48.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,你肯定会的 行吧\N{\fs90}Yeah, you are. OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.94,0:47:51.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,他的确是这么做的\N{\fs90}He did.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.25,0:47:54.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个叫做变向漂移\N{\fs90}This is called transitioning--
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.55,0:47:57.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,先漂向一个方向 然后再漂向另一个方向\N{\fs90}drifting the car one way and then the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.02,0:48:01.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,做得好的话堪比芭蕾舞般优雅\N{\fs90}Get it right and it's almost balletic.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.80,0:48:09.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,太优美了\N{\fs90}That is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.73,0:48:12.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,从这样到这样 无缝衔接\N{\fs90}From that to that, seamlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.20,0:48:18.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而 接下来的就不怎么优雅了\N{\fs90}Which, sadly, couldn't be said of what followed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.67,0:48:20.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,刹车\N{\fs90}Brake!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.42,0:48:29.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,刹车 刹车 刹车\N{\fs90}Brake, brake, brake.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.42,0:48:32.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 该死的\N{\fs90}Oh, bollocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.33,0:48:38.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,宝马知道我们用他们的车吗\N{\fs90}Does BMW know we're using their car?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.56,0:48:40.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不知道吧 -好吧\N{\fs90}- I don't think so. - OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.23,0:48:43.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,终于功夫不负有心人\N{\fs90}Eventually, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.24,0:48:48.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,耶\N{\fs90}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.28,0:48:57.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 这就是变向漂移\N{\fs90}Yes, that was a transition.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.98,0:48:59.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,你的第一次\N{\fs90}Your first.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.88,0:49:06.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,一天结束 我已经驾轻就熟\N{\fs90}By the end of the day, I really had got it mastered.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.36,0:49:10.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是我第一次化身为\N{\fs90}I'd become, for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.06,0:49:12.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,一位车神\N{\fs90}a driving god.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.17,0:49:20.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的\N{\fs90}It really is...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.77,0:49:23.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,当你给油恰到好处\N{\fs90}It really is the most amazing feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.51,0:49:25.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,让后轮漂起来的时候\N{\fs90}when you get just the right amount of power
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.27,0:49:26.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,那感觉实在太妙了\N{\fs90}to spin the back wheels,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.81,0:49:28.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,但不要给太多油 不然车就要打转了\N{\fs90}but not so much that you don't spin the whole car,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.01,0:49:30.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,要控制在临界点上\N{\fs90}and you hold it on the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.85,0:49:33.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,等会 不好意思 他去法国回来\N{\fs90}No, I'm sorry, I'm sorry. He came back from France,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.28,0:49:35.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,就一天\N{\fs90}where he'd spent one day
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.45,0:49:36.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后就说 "我现在厉害了"\N{\fs90}saying, "Well, I'm brilliant now."
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.85,0:49:37.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,对啊 我就是\N{\fs90}Yeah, well, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.02,0:49:39.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是 对不起啊\N{\fs90}Well, now, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.19,0:49:41.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 我花了十年时间\N{\fs90}Hammond, it took me ten years
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.52,0:49:43.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,才学会如何漂移\N{\fs90}to learn how to drift a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.29,0:49:44.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,-嗯哼 -十...\N{\fs90}- Mm-hm. Mm-hm. - Ten--
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.59,0:49:45.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,但因为我不是头猩猩\N{\fs90}But because I'm not an ape,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.06,0:49:48.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,我一天就学会了\N{\fs90}I did it in one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.60,0:49:49.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,-才没有 -我就是\N{\fs90}- You didn't! - Well, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.93,0:49:51.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,好了好了 这不重要\N{\fs90}Look, anyway, it doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.43,0:49:54.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了看看他是不是车神\N{\fs90}To find out if he was a driving god,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.47,0:49:56.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,我和克拉克森为理查德哈蒙德\N{\fs90}Clarkson and I arranged for Richard Hammond
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.61,0:49:59.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,安排了一次漂移赛\N{\fs90}to take part in a drifting contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.77,0:50:01.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 我们为他准备了车\N{\fs90}Yeah, we did. We fixed up the car for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.71,0:50:03.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,也安排好了对手\N{\fs90}We fixed up the competitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.48,0:50:04.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,万事俱备\N{\fs90}We did everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.55,0:50:13.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是这辆车\N{\fs90}This is the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.39,0:50:16.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,它原本是一辆日产200SX\N{\fs90}It started out as a Nissan 200SX,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.29,0:50:21.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是配备了700马力的6.2升V8引擎\N{\fs90}but it's been fitted with a 700-horsepower 6.2L V8
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.63,0:50:23.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,和一个改装的转向器\N{\fs90}and a modified steering rack,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.03,0:50:25.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以它能这样\N{\fs90}so it can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.92,0:50:52.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,它的车主 史蒂夫·"巴格西"·比亚乔尼\N{\fs90}Its owner, a chap called Steve "Baggsy" Biagioni,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.83,0:50:55.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,他说 为了给我的比赛做准备\N{\fs90}said that, to prepare for my competition,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.13,0:50:59.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,我需要在一排标志桶上放上西瓜\N{\fs90}I needed to put some melons on a row of traffic cones.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.43,0:51:00.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是要干嘛\N{\fs90}What are we doing with these?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.94,0:51:02.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,我能放下来吗 这些瓜太沉了\N{\fs90}Can I put mine down? They're really heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.90,0:51:04.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,在漂移赛里\N{\fs90}Well, in a drifting competition,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.51,0:51:05.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,有一种近切点\N{\fs90}you have what's called clipping points.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.74,0:51:07.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,-嗯 -这些点是\N{\fs90}- Yes. - So these would be
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.61,0:51:09.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,裁判们在赛道上设置的点\N{\fs90}determined points on the track
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.38,0:51:12.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们想在那里观察车辆\N{\fs90}made by the judges as to where they want to see the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.11,0:51:15.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,-近切点是西瓜吗 -对的 西瓜\N{\fs90}- Our clipping points are melons? - Melons, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.02,0:51:17.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的要求是\N{\fs90}My orders were to get
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.55,0:51:19.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,尽可能地靠近那些瓜\N{\fs90}as close to the melons as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.52,0:51:22.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,但又不撞到它们\N{\fs90}without hitting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.69,0:51:24.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们要集中注意力\N{\fs90}We're just gonna concentrate
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.26,0:51:26.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,寻找赛道的中央位置\N{\fs90}on looking for the middle of the track, yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.96,0:51:29.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且把车尾指向瓜的附近\N{\fs90}and aim the back of the car near them melons.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.90,0:51:30.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\fs90}OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.50,0:51:34.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 准备好的话就上吧\N{\fs90}Right, when you're ready, go for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.48,0:51:42.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,该死的\N{\fs90}Bollocks!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.61,0:51:48.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,我还完全没有掌握技巧...\N{\fs90}Having not really mastered this at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.48,0:51:52.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的天\N{\fs90}Oh, shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.49,0:51:53.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,大猩猩和船长\N{\fs90}...it was time for the event
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.06,0:51:58.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,组织的赛事就要开始了\N{\fs90}organised by Clarkson and May to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.69,0:52:01.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们告诉我到这儿报到\N{\fs90}What they've done is told me to report here,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.56,0:52:02.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,罗金汉姆赛道\N{\fs90}Rockingham Raceway,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.80,0:52:04.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这里他们安排了\N{\fs90}where they've arranged for me
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.43,0:52:05.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,我和两位漂移车手\N{\fs90}to take on two drifters
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.77,0:52:07.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,一起进行漂移赛\N{\fs90}in some competitive drifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.94,0:52:15.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,比赛路线是由一系列经典的变向漂移弯组成\N{\fs90}The course was a series of classic transitional bends...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.44,0:52:16.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,巧妙的布满了\N{\fs90}strategically peppered
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.91,0:52:18.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,一些令人生畏的近切点\N{\fs90}with the dreaded clipping points.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.08,0:52:25.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,巴格西要向我解释如何计分\N{\fs90}Baggsy was on hand to explain how the scoring worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.29,0:52:28.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,漂移赛是以裁判为核心的运动\N{\fs90}The main thing about drifting is that it's a judged sport,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.29,0:52:31.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,裁判设置近切点的地方就是他们想观察车辆的地方\N{\fs90}and the judges have placed the clipping points where they want to see the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.06,0:52:35.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以不是车头就是车尾\N{\fs90}So that'll either be the rear or the front of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.73,0:52:37.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,你离近切点越近\N{\fs90}The closer you get to the clipping points,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.27,0:52:39.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,你得的分数就越多\N{\fs90}the more points you're gonna get awarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.70,0:52:41.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,但最重要的是不要撞到它们\N{\fs90}But the key is to not hit them.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.50,0:52:42.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你能擦过它们\N{\fs90}If you can brush them,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.80,0:52:44.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,你就能得到最高的分数\N{\fs90}you're gonna get maximum points.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.21,0:52:45.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说的"擦过"\N{\fs90}When I say "brush",
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.37,0:52:46.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,是要不能把它们撞翻\N{\fs90}I mean don't knock them over.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.54,0:52:47.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你能够\N{\fs90}If you can be
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.61,0:52:48.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,保持半米以内的距离\N{\fs90}within half a metre,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.68,0:52:51.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,你就能得高分\N{\fs90}you're gonna score high.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.25,0:52:53.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我也可以通过保持华丽的漂移\N{\fs90}I'd also score points for holding the car
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.02,0:52:56.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,来获取额外的分数\N{\fs90}in as impressive a drift as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.02,0:52:59.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,你还要记住持续给油\N{\fs90}You've got to keep the throttle in
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.69,0:53:02.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,就你就可以在漂移的时候保持一个良好的角度\N{\fs90}so that you maintain the drift with good angle,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.16,0:53:04.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,而这只跟你打了多少方向\N{\fs90}and that's only up to you about how much steering input
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.69,0:53:06.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,和给了多少油门有关\N{\fs90}and how much accelerator you put in.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.90,0:53:10.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,赛车被设计成能以接近90°角漂移\N{\fs90}The cars are designed to run at almost 90°.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.73,0:53:12.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们的转向角非常大\N{\fs90}They've got massive amounts of steering angle,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.90,0:53:14.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,这样直到赛道最后你也可以照样开\N{\fs90}so you can drive on the end of your rack.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.97,0:53:17.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 所以我开得很快的话\N{\fs90}OK. So I don't get awarded points
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.51,0:53:18.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,有没有额外的奖励分\N{\fs90}for how quickly I do the whole thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.97,0:53:20.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 速度没有影响\N{\fs90}No, that doesn't come into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.41,0:53:23.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,只有角度和走线才重要\N{\fs90}It's all about angle, line,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.68,0:53:25.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有你有多少观赏性\N{\fs90}and how much you excite everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.68,0:53:27.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是看谁能秀一脸 是吧\N{\fs90}It's judged showing off, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.98,0:53:30.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,-基本上是的 -行吧\N{\fs90}- Basically, yeah. - Yeah, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.25,0:53:34.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,当我的赛车正在为参赛做准备的时候\N{\fs90}As my car was prepped for the big event,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.02,0:53:37.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的同事安排的竞争对手\N{\fs90}the competitors, organised by my colleagues,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.73,0:53:40.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,终于来了\N{\fs90}finally arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.29,0:53:44.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,而他们和我想象的不太一样\N{\fs90}And they weren't what I was expecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.63,0:53:46.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,看起来詹姆斯和杰里米\N{\fs90}It seems James and Jeremy
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.20,0:53:49.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,还是希望他们的老同事能赢的\N{\fs90}want their old mate to do well after all,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.34,0:53:51.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为 如果我没看错的话\N{\fs90}because, unless I'm mistaken,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.97,0:53:55.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的对手是一个小孩\N{\fs90}it would appear that I'm up against a child
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.54,0:53:57.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有一个没有胳膊的人\N{\fs90}and a man with no arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.28,0:54:01.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\fs90}OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.55,0:54:03.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是我今天的比赛\N{\fs90}That's my competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.36,0:54:10.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,裁判们已就位\N{\fs90}With the judges in position,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.12,0:54:13.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,比赛就要开始了\N{\fs90}it was time for the contest to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.70,0:54:16.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,首先登场的是这位残疾的先生\N{\fs90}First up was the disabled gentleman,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.57,0:54:18.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,来自波兰的巴泰克·奥斯塔沃斯基\N{\fs90}Bartek Ostatowski from Poland.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.30,0:54:21.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,实际上 巴泰克...\N{\fs90}The fact is, Bartek...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.97,0:54:26.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,他的上肢部分有两处缺陷\N{\fs90}is deficient in the arms department to the tune of two.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.04,0:54:29.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说的"缺陷" 我不是指缺陷\N{\fs90}When I say "deficient", I don't mean deficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.34,0:54:30.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,他...\N{\fs90}He... He has...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.41,0:54:32.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,他根本就没有上肢\N{\fs90}He has no arms... at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.38,0:54:34.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我想说 他能敢于参加已经很了不起了\N{\fs90}So, I mean, it's brilliant that he's having a go.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.88,0:54:36.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的 太伟大了\N{\fs90}Really, it's tremendous.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.02,0:54:40.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,巴泰克在一场摩托车事故中失去双臂\N{\fs90}Bartek, who lost his arms in a motorcycling accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.29,0:54:43.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,但却克服困难 用脚打方向\N{\fs90}overcomes his disability by steering with his foot
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.93,0:54:46.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且用肩膀换挡\N{\fs90}and changing gear with his shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.13,0:54:52.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,对我来说不幸的是 他非常擅长\N{\fs90}And unfortunately for me, he's rather good at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.42,0:55:11.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,他是怎么...\N{\fs90}How is he...?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.48,0:55:37.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,好样的\N{\fs90}Good for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.75,0:55:39.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,真是好样的\N{\fs90}Really good for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.25,0:55:42.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,耶 很好\N{\fs90}Yeah! Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.12,0:55:44.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,感觉非常好\N{\fs90}This was nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.19,0:55:46.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,满分是30分\N{\fs90}Out of a maximum of 30 points,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.55,0:55:50.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,裁判给了巴泰克22分\N{\fs90}the judges awarded Bartek a score of 22.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.83,0:55:54.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后轮到那个小孩了\N{\fs90}And then it was the turn of the child,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.86,0:55:58.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,康纳·夏拿汉 只有13岁\N{\fs90}Conor Shanahan, who's just 13 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.54,0:56:03.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,要来了 康纳的小学生漂移\N{\fs90}Here we go. Primary-school drifting with Conor.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.84,0:56:05.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,他也就开10米就会没兴趣了\N{\fs90}He'll go ten yards, get bored,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.44,0:56:06.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后哭着找妈妈\N{\fs90}and start crying for his mummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.88,0:56:10.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而...\N{\fs90}However...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.19,0:56:29.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,他才13岁啊 还有5年才能有选举权啊\N{\fs90}He's 13! I mean, he's five years off voting!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.13,0:57:01.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,裁判给了这个嘚瑟的小杂...\N{\fs90}The judges awarded the cocky little sh...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.86,0:57:04.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,小天才27分\N{\fs90}talented young man a score of 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.50,0:57:08.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后轮到我了\N{\fs90}And then it was my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.60,0:57:11.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,好 胜负在此一举了\N{\fs90}Right, this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.74,0:57:13.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,见证荣耀的时刻\N{\fs90}My shot at glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.78,0:57:16.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,我所有的才学\N{\fs90}Everything I'd learned
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.21,0:57:18.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,都会展现在聚光灯下\N{\fs90}would be brought into sharp focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.75,0:57:20.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,给油 给油 给油\N{\fs90}Gas, gas, gas, gas, gas!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.48,0:57:24.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,最重要的是不要撞到它们\N{\fs90}The key is to not hit them.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.35,0:57:27.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在 就是见证奇迹的时刻\N{\fs90}Here, in the moment of truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.19,0:57:32.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在等黄灯 来了\N{\fs90}I'm waiting for amber. There it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.33,0:57:33.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,黄灯然后...\N{\fs90}Amber and...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.60,0:57:43.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了Grand Tour荣耀前进的\N{\fs90}forward to glory for Grand Tour!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.57,0:57:45.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,弹离合\N{\fs90}Clutch kick!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.87,0:58:12.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 糟了\N{\fs90}Oh, shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.90,0:58:15.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,冲过终点\N{\fs90}Oh! And across the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.64,0:58:16.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,耶\N{\fs90}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.81,0:58:18.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,耶 我打翻了旗子\N{\fs90}Yeah, I clipped the flag.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.24,0:58:20.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想这可能会额外加一分\N{\fs90}That's probably an extra point, I imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.44,0:58:21.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,额...我再点一次火\N{\fs90}Erm... I'll just restart,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.81,0:58:24.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我还想在那儿停一下\N{\fs90}because I wanted to stop there for a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.71,0:58:26.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 噢 我又熄火了\N{\fs90}Yep. Oh, I've stalled again.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.25,0:58:32.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\fs90}Yep. Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.72,0:58:34.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢大家\N{\fs90}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.86,0:58:37.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以说...\N{\fs90}So...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.29,0:58:40.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,等一下 你最终得分是多少\N{\fs90}Hold on. What was your final score?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.90,0:58:43.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,两分\N{\fs90}Two.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.36,0:58:44.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,-只有两分 -是的\N{\fs90}- Two? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.43,0:58:45.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,你太渣了\N{\fs90}You were useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.43,0:58:47.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 听着 伙计们\N{\fs90}No, listen, gentlemen. Gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.57,0:58:49.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,我必须得说 我很高兴\N{\fs90}I have to say, I'm delighted
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.34,0:58:52.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,你已经掌握了漂移技巧 尽管不多\N{\fs90}that you now have, albeit limited, drifting skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.17,0:58:54.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为这意味着我有了一个玩伴\N{\fs90}cos it means I have a playmate,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.31,0:58:59.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,就像下面这个过去12周的剪辑所展现的\N{\fs90}as this short montage from the last 12 weeks shows.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.73,0:59:20.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,是吧 看到了吗\N{\fs90}Yeah, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.94,0:59:25.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 就在临界点上\N{\fs90}Yeah. Yeah. On the edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.17,0:59:27.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 我承认这不是...\N{\fs90}Now, I admit... I admit it's not...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.88,0:59:29.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,这的确不是什么有价值的事\N{\fs90}It's not important work, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.38,0:59:31.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,对 我们并没有找到什么疾病的解药\N{\fs90}No, we haven't actually cured anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.15,0:59:32.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们也没给战乱地区\N{\fs90}No, we haven't brought peace
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.58,0:59:34.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,带来和平之类的\N{\fs90}to troubled parts of the world or any of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.48,0:59:35.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,是 但这好歹也算个差事\N{\fs90}No, but it is a job.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.88,0:59:38.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是个差事 而我们很擅长这个差事\N{\fs90}It is a job, and we're very good at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.15,0:59:39.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不 你们不擅长 -我们擅长\N{\fs90}- No, you're not very good at it. - We are.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.02,0:59:41.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 我这里有几段\N{\fs90}No, well, I've got some items
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.06,0:59:44.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,回收站里找到的未播出的镜头\N{\fs90}from the unseen footage bin
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.16,0:59:45.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,那上面可不是这么说的\N{\fs90}that would suggest otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.06,0:59:47.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,很抱歉 我们没时间看了\N{\fs90}Unfortunately, we don't have time for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.93,0:59:49.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,可惜 太可惜了\N{\fs90}Sadly. Cor, that's a pity!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.36,0:59:50.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 你错了 我们还有时间\N{\fs90}No, no. You're wrong. We do have time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.93,0:59:52.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,谁想看那些视频吗 没人\N{\fs90}Who wants to see that? Nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.04,0:59:57.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 我们来看\N{\fs90}OK. Let's roll it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.34,0:59:59.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是理查德·哈蒙德\N{\fs90}Here is Richard Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.07,1:00:01.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,他能驾驭170匹马力吗\N{\fs90}Can he contain 170 horsepower?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.61,1:00:04.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 看起来不行\N{\fs90}No, it would appear not.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.25,1:00:06.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,杰里米·克拉克森 保时捷911 GT3\N{\fs90}Jeremy Clarkson, Porsche 911 GT3.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.25,1:00:07.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 看到了吗\N{\fs90}Oh, there we go. You see
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.49,1:00:09.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,我有点玩脱了\N{\fs90}I have actually made a mess of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.15,1:00:11.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的你玩脱了 我们看见了\N{\fs90}Yes, you have, and we saw it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.42,1:00:13.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德和留你名弯较劲\N{\fs90}Richard Hammond negotiating Your Name Here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.35,1:00:14.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,你当时的名字\N{\fs90}Your name, in this instance,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.96,1:00:16.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,显然是大白痴啊\N{\fs90}is Total Bell End, it would appear.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.49,1:00:19.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,大猩猩 他驯服GT3了吗\N{\fs90}Clarkson, has he tamed the GT3?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.93,1:00:20.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,才没有\N{\fs90}No!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.00,1:00:22.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,我有个想法 等着\N{\fs90}I've had an idea. Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.03,1:00:24.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,我猜你不是这么想的\N{\fs90}I bet it wasn't this.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.77,1:00:29.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,看好了 准备\N{\fs90}Watch this. Ready?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.40,1:00:30.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,千万别立flag\N{\fs90}Never say that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.80,1:00:33.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,就算你只是开着家用四门轿车\N{\fs90}Even if you're just in a four-door family saloon,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.54,1:00:35.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,也会变成灾难\N{\fs90}it's disastrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.14,1:00:37.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 理查德哈蒙德他这回能行了吗\N{\fs90}Right, Richard Hammond, has he got it yet?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.58,1:00:40.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 我觉得他成功了 好的\N{\fs90}Yes, I think he has. Yes! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.85,1:00:43.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 他还是没成功\N{\fs90}No. No, he hasn't got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.65,1:00:45.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我跟你说 -人无完人\N{\fs90}- I tell you what - Nobody's perfect!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.02,1:00:50.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,-就那么几次 -嗯 大概两次 三次 四次 五次这样\N{\fs90}- A couple of moments. - Yeah, just two or three, four, five.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.59,1:00:52.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,别担心\N{\fs90}Don't worry. Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.29,1:00:53.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,以后 我们会找\N{\fs90}In the future, we'll just get
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.76,1:00:55.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,一个没胳膊的人和一个小孩来做这些\N{\fs90}an armless man and small boy to do those bits.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.83,1:00:57.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,闭嘴\N{\fs90}Shut up! Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.50,1:00:59.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,而不是让一个胖子和一个小孩来做是吗\N{\fs90}As opposed to a fat man and a small boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.57,1:01:01.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管怎样...\N{\fs90}Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.40,1:01:03.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,听着 在这糟糕的失望中\N{\fs90}Listen, on that terrible disappointment,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.17,1:01:05.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,不仅到了本集节目的结尾\N{\fs90}it is time to end not just the show
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.57,1:01:06.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,也到了我们这一季节目的尾声了\N{\fs90}but the entire series.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.84,1:01:08.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,非常感谢大家的观看\N{\fs90}Thank you so much for watching.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.14,1:01:09.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,感谢你们的到来\N{\fs90}Thank you all for coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.98,1:01:11.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,今年的晚些时候\N{\fs90}And we'll see you later in the year
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.98,1:01:13.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们再跟大家见面\N{\fs90}for more of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.78,1:01:14.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,大家保重 再见\N{\fs90}Take care. Goodbye.
